receipts, transcribing interviews.

278
00:18:15,895 --> 00:18:17,889
Is this seriously all you've written?

279
00:18:18,135 --> 00:18:19,375
This isn't mine.

280
00:18:19,871 --> 00:18:22,035
Sorry, but Mr. Suga's out right now.

281
00:18:23,418 --> 00:18:27,978
Sometimes, I got to ride around town with
Miss Natsumi to assist with the interviews.

282
00:18:44,983 --> 00:18:47,381
They're looking for a real-life sunshine girl.

283
00:18:47,406 --> 00:18:48,915
That's so hilarious.

284
00:18:48,971 --> 00:18:51,403
My little sister's friend's a real sunshine girl.

285
00:18:51,571 --> 00:18:53,889
People will call her up right before they go on a date.

286
00:18:53,914 --> 00:18:55,963
We really don't do those kind of interviews.

287
00:18:55,988 --> 00:18:59,937
After that, the balloon's particle
imager picked up something really strange.

288
00:19:00,245 --> 00:19:03,319
A swarm of moving objects from among the cumulonimbi.

289
00:19:04,225 --> 00:19:05,926
Is this seriously all you've managed to write?

290
00:19:05,950 --> 00:19:07,831
You should wait for these to go on sale.

291
00:19:07,856 --> 00:19:09,460
Mr. Suga's out right now.

292
00:19:09,485 --> 00:19:10,664
This paragraph's crap.

293
00:19:10,688 --> 00:19:12,099
But this one here's not too bad.

294
00:19:12,124 --> 00:19:12,562
Oh.

295
00:19:14,959 --> 00:19:17,320
Come on, Mr. Suga. We got to go.

296
00:19:17,439 --> 00:19:18,359
Wake up.

297
00:19:23,454 --> 00:19:25,502
My days were, well, hectic.

298
00:19:25,630 --> 00:19:27,267
But for the first time in my life,

299
00:19:27,346 --> 00:19:30,070
someone counted on me, and it was nice.

300
00:19:30,142 --> 00:19:33,740
Those rainy days in Tokyo seemed to just fly by.

301
00:19:51,035 --> 00:19:53,299
Rain. Rain.

302
00:19:53,897 --> 00:19:55,500
Rain. Rain.

303
00:19:56,994 --> 00:19:58,209
There you are.

304
00:19:58,784 --> 00:19:59,769
Hey there, Rain.

305
00:19:59,831 --> 00:20:00,802
Are you good?

306
00:20:01,890 --> 00:20:03,565
Is that so? Here.

307
00:20:06,571 --> 00:20:08,509
Don't you worry your pretty head.

308
00:20:08,564 --> 00:20:10,080
I'm telling you, it's an easy job.

309
00:20:10,105 --> 00:20:10,907
We'll see.

310
00:20:12,917 --> 00:20:14,617
Just try it and see how you like it.

311
00:20:14,823 --> 00:20:16,586
You'll get paid immediately after.

312
00:20:16,873 --> 00:20:18,430
Our club's right over there.

313
00:20:21,035 --> 00:20:22,170
I know her.

314
00:20:27,097 --> 00:20:30,838
You might as well give it a go
and earn some quick cash, huh?

315
00:20:32,864 --> 00:20:34,851
It's just right through that door, okay?

316
00:20:34,876 --> 00:20:35,931
Come on, let's go.

317
00:20:38,822 --> 00:20:39,417
But...

318
00:20:48,603 --> 00:20:49,485
Hey!

319
00:20:50,437 --> 00:20:51,445
Let's go!

320
00:20:53,323 --> 00:20:54,902
What? No, no, no, no.

321
00:20:54,927 --> 00:20:55,864
Where are they going?

322
00:21:01,628 --> 00:21:03,599
Hey! Wait, please!

323
00:21:03,699 --> 00:21:04,760
Just keep running!

324
00:21:04,784 --> 00:21:05,772
No, wait!

325
00:21:10,238 --> 00:21:10,945
Punk!

326
00:21:14,068 --> 00:21:16,308
Hey. Where you think you're going, buddy?

327
00:21:16,752 --> 00:21:18,953
What in the hell do you think you're doing?!

328
00:21:20,175 --> 00:21:21,508
You were about to force her t-to... to...

329
00:21:21,532 --> 00:21:21,807
Huh?

330
00:21:21,956 --> 00:21:23,331
What are you, dumb?

331
00:21:23,895 --> 00:21:26,572
Hate to break it to you, but she and I made a deal.

332
00:21:29,058 --> 00:21:30,161
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

333
00:21:30,186 --> 00:21:32,617
Wait a second. You look familiar.

334
00:21:33,204 --> 00:21:35,341
You were squatting in front of our club.

335
00:21:35,709 --> 00:21:38,266
What is this, some kind of payback?

336
00:21:38,386 --> 00:21:40,459
Please, stop hitting him.

337
00:21:41,675 --> 00:21:42,687
I said stop!

338
00:21:42,711 --> 00:21:43,612
Damn you!

339
00:21:43,637 --> 00:21:45,082
Get off me!

340
00:21:47,721 --> 00:21:50,389
What do you got there? A toy?

341
00:21:51,796 --> 00:21:53,838
You really are dumb.

342
00:22:17,738 --> 00:22:18,809
Get up.

343
00:22:19,635 --> 00:22:20,748
Come on!

344
00:22:42,758 --> 00:22:43,321
Hey!

345
00:22:44,670 --> 00:22:46,164
What'd you do that for?

346
00:22:46,260 --> 00:22:48,032
Paying me back for the burger?

347
00:22:48,286 --> 00:22:48,793
Huh?

348
00:22:49,279 --> 00:22:50,350
Who are you?

349
00:22:50,606 --> 00:22:51,933
And where'd you get that gun?

350
00:22:52,037 --> 00:22:53,187
That was just...

351
00:22:53,528 --> 00:22:58,096
I-I found it. I-I thought it was a
toy, and it brought me luck, so I kept it.

352
00:22:58,416 --> 00:22:59,682
That's your reason?

353
00:22:59,838 --> 00:23:01,594
How could you point it at someone?

354
00:23:01,696 --> 00:23:03,330
You could have killed him!

355
00:23:04,199 --> 00:23:06,519
Seriously, who does that?

356
00:23:06,558 --> 00:23:07,598
It's messed up.

357
00:23:42,202 --> 00:23:43,321
So, uh...

358
00:23:44,392 --> 00:23:45,965
I ended up getting fired.

359
00:23:46,417 --> 00:23:47,544
'Cause of me?

360
00:23:47,833 --> 00:23:50,176
It didn't have anything to do with the burger.

361
00:23:50,311 --> 00:23:53,361
Since I got fired, I needed the money,

362
00:23:53,798 --> 00:23:55,292
so, um...

363
00:23:55,403 --> 00:23:57,373
I'm sorry. I-I shouldn't have...

364
00:24:04,620 --> 00:24:06,327
Hey. Does it hurt?

365
00:24:06,352 --> 00:24:07,456
No, not really.

366
00:24:08,872 --> 00:24:10,920
Let me guess... You ran away from home?

367
00:24:10,945 --> 00:24:11,532
Huh?

368
00:24:11,786 --> 00:24:13,177
It's pretty obvious.

369
00:24:13,732 --> 00:24:16,625
Too bad you can't enjoy Tokyo with all this rain.

370
00:24:16,719 --> 00:24:18,403
Uh, yeah.

371
00:24:19,294 --> 00:24:20,005
Come with me.

372
00:24:20,029 --> 00:24:20,413
Uh...

373
00:24:29,558 --> 00:24:30,258
Whoa.

374
00:24:39,596 --> 00:24:40,357
Watch.

375
00:24:40,469 --> 00:24:41,661
It's gonna clear up.

376
00:24:41,863 --> 00:24:42,438
Huh?

377
00:24:55,349 --> 00:24:57,303
Hey. What do you mean by...

378
00:25:08,775 --> 00:25:10,016
What?

379
00:25:13,217 --> 00:25:14,536
You're a sunshine girl.

380
00:25:16,657 --> 00:25:17,987
My name's Hina.

381
00:25:18,278 --> 00:25:18,986
And you?

382
00:25:19,137 --> 00:25:19,905
Hodaka.

383
00:25:19,930 --> 00:25:20,424
How old?

384
00:25:20,710 --> 00:25:21,757
Uh, 16.

385
00:25:21,853 --> 00:25:23,259
Mm...

386
00:25:23,426 --> 00:25:24,703
You're younger than me.

387
00:25:24,727 --> 00:25:25,079
Huh?

388
00:25:25,126 --> 00:25:27,274
I'll be 18 in, uh...

389
00:25:27,768 --> 00:25:28,839
approximately a month.

390
00:25:28,903 --> 00:25:30,418
You-you look younger.

391
00:25:30,568 --> 00:25:32,120
So you should treat me with respect.

392
00:25:32,596 --> 00:25:33,612
What?

393
00:25:34,533 --> 00:25:36,630
Mm...

394
00:25:40,119 --> 00:25:41,867
Nice to meet you, Hodaka.

395
00:26:26,716 --> 00:26:28,677
Huh?

396
00:26:33,352 --> 00:26:34,717
Mommy, I saw a fish.

397
00:26:34,788 --> 00:26:36,656
Oh, yeah? That's nice.

398
00:26:37,473 --> 00:26:39,269
You better not be making this up.

399
00:26:39,682 --> 00:26:42,223
I'm dead serious. Come on, this way.

400
00:26:46,086 --> 00:26:47,555
Look. It's over there.

401
00:26:48,635 --> 00:26:49,795
What am I looking at?

402
00:26:49,819 --> 00:26:50,956
It's right over there.

403
00:26:51,019 --> 00:26:52,386
Just trust me, will you?

404
00:26:57,646 --> 00:26:58,262
Huh?

405
00:26:58,337 --> 00:26:59,194
Mm.

406
00:27:05,248 --> 00:27:06,774
What the heck is that?

407
00:27:23,268 --> 00:27:24,980
And in our storm watch series,

408
00:27:25,079 --> 00:27:29,480
the Kanto region is experiencing a
record-breaking amount of rainfall this summer.

409
00:27:29,513 --> 00:27:32,949
It has been raining continuously
for more than two months now.

410
00:27:33,096 --> 00:27:37,631
And our 30-day forecast predicts more
heavy rain for at least another month.

411
00:27:38,464 --> 00:27:43,312
The Meteorological Agency is calling for strict
alerts on landslides and other related disasters,

412
00:27:43,337 --> 00:27:46,888
as these are extremely unusual
weather patterns for this season.

413
00:27:46,913 --> 00:27:48,168
Is that too expensive?

414
00:27:49,271 --> 00:27:51,040
Oh, my God. Come look at this.

415
00:27:52,100 --> 00:27:52,561
Huh?

416
00:27:52,586 --> 00:27:54,172
It's amazing.

417
00:27:55,229 --> 00:27:57,184
It's so weird.

418
00:28:00,298 --> 00:28:01,050
Hmm.

419
00:28:01,560 --> 00:28:03,673
I mean, they do kind of look like fish.

420
00:28:04,223 --> 00:28:06,221
Except these things come from the sky,

421
00:28:06,653 --> 00:28:08,973
and it's not like they leave behind evidence.

422
00:28:08,998 --> 00:28:11,327
I know. They just instantly disappear. Look.

423
00:28:14,218 --> 00:28:15,107
Huh?

424
00:28:15,569 --> 00:28:18,412
And remember what that guy we interviewed said?

425
00:28:18,467 --> 00:28:21,391
The sky's a more vast unknown world than even the sea.

426
00:28:22,272 --> 00:28:26,809
A cumulonimbus can hold as much water as
an entire lake. Which means it's possible

427
00:28:26,834 --> 00:28:29,367
that it could hold a whole unknown ecosystem.

428
00:28:29,725 --> 00:28:30,664
Something like...

429
00:28:30,989 --> 00:28:31,826
like these fish.

430
00:28:31,850 --> 00:28:32,608
Yeah, totally.

431
00:28:32,642 --> 00:28:33,920
That's so cool!

432
00:28:34,271 --> 00:28:35,717
If we write about it...

433
00:28:36,222 --> 00:28:38,473
oh, maybe we can make good money from it.

434
00:28:38,498 --> 00:28:39,560
Huh? What's...

435
00:28:39,782 --> 00:28:40,151
Huh?

436
00:28:40,175 --> 00:28:42,615
- Oh, come on. You're starting to sound like Kei.

437
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:44,917
You don't want to wind up a boring grown-up.

438
00:28:44,967 --> 00:28:47,681
Careful, or that sunshine girl is gonna lose interest.

439
00:28:47,820 --> 00:28:48,996
You two are going on a date, right?

440
00:28:49,021 --> 00:28:50,536
It's not a date. I'm just confirming if...

441
00:28:50,561 --> 00:28:52,482
Well, I got a job interview, so...

442
00:28:52,594 --> 00:28:54,809
What? Don't you work here?

443
00:28:54,834 --> 00:28:56,312
This is just a temporary thing.

444
00:29:01,714 --> 00:29:03,922
I told you guys, it's not a date.

445
00:29:05,503 --> 00:29:08,117
I understand how you feel, Keisuke.

446
00:29:08,189 --> 00:29:12,517
But we've finally gotten to the point
where she isn't asking about you constantly.

447
00:29:13,294 --> 00:29:16,490
It would be too cruel to her to
allow you to meet with her now.

448
00:29:16,515 --> 00:29:19,094
That's not... It's well within my rights to see her.

449
00:29:19,129 --> 00:29:22,726
Well, let me ask... You still smoke, right?

450
00:29:23,068 --> 00:29:23,503
Huh?

451
00:29:23,527 --> 00:29:24,657
She has asthma.

452
00:29:25,006 --> 00:29:26,040
You know that.

453
00:29:26,532 --> 00:29:28,070
Selfish, don't you think?

454
00:29:28,336 --> 00:29:30,372
Actually, not anymore.

455
00:29:30,591 --> 00:29:31,869
I've already quit.

456
00:29:31,893 --> 00:29:32,786
Perhaps.

457
00:29:33,309 --> 00:29:35,788
Still, that doesn't address your lifestyle.

458
00:29:36,066 --> 00:29:36,685
Huh?

459
00:29:45,386 --> 00:29:47,856
Besides, with all this rain now,

460
00:29:48,007 --> 00:29:49,683
she can't play outside.

461
00:29:49,738 --> 00:29:51,494
It would be bad for her asthma.

462
00:29:52,822 --> 00:29:54,998
I feel sorry for children nowadays.

463
00:29:55,125 --> 00:29:58,723
We used to have such beautiful springs and summers.

464
00:30:11,104 --> 00:30:13,882
They can't go on living there unsupervised like that.

465
00:30:13,995 --> 00:30:16,061
I completely agree.

466
00:30:22,374 --> 00:30:23,213
Wait a minute.

467
00:30:24,405 --> 00:30:25,778
Could this possibly be...

468
00:30:27,160 --> 00:30:30,178
the first time I'm visiting...

469
00:30:30,774 --> 00:30:32,036
a girl's home?

470
00:30:34,350 --> 00:30:35,733
Welcome to my place.

471
00:30:35,845 --> 00:30:36,661
Was it hard to find?

472
00:30:36,686 --> 00:30:38,107
Uh, I just stopped to, uh...

473
00:30:38,132 --> 00:30:39,420
It's-it's not much. Here.

474
00:30:40,285 --> 00:30:41,515
That was very sweet of you.

475
00:30:42,088 --> 00:30:42,826
Welcome.

476
00:30:43,891 --> 00:30:44,399
Thanks.

477
00:30:44,713 --> 00:30:45,518
Sure thing.

478
00:30:49,963 --> 00:30:51,822
Hodaka, have you had lunch yet?

479
00:30:51,893 --> 00:30:52,934
No, not yet.

480
00:30:52,990 --> 00:30:54,744
But you don't have to.

481
00:30:54,769 --> 00:30:55,122
Uh...

482
00:30:55,146 --> 00:30:56,358
You just sit right there.

483
00:30:56,620 --> 00:30:58,185
Hey, mind if I use these?

484
00:30:58,241 --> 00:30:59,187
Yeah. No, sure.

485
00:30:59,604 --> 00:31:00,348
Thanks.

486
00:31:13,423 --> 00:31:15,751
So, do you live all by yourself here, Hina?

487
00:31:16,029 --> 00:31:18,873
With my younger brother, due to some circumstances.

488
00:31:19,082 --> 00:31:20,547
Circumstances?

489
00:31:21,208 --> 00:31:23,638
How about you? Why did you run away?

490
00:31:25,349 --> 00:31:28,144
Truth is everything was suffocating.

491
00:31:28,302 --> 00:31:30,242
That town, my parents.

492
00:31:30,679 --> 00:31:32,094
I see.

493
00:31:40,348 --> 00:31:42,548
You should go back, don't you think?

494
00:31:44,145 --> 00:31:45,615
No, I don't want to.

495
00:31:46,146 --> 00:31:47,180
I see.

496
00:31:49,287 --> 00:31:51,210
Here you go. Lunch is served.

497
00:31:51,765 --> 00:31:52,543
Whoa.

498
00:31:53,355 --> 00:31:56,039
I forgot the spring onions. Where'd I put them?

499
00:31:58,146 --> 00:32:01,131
So, how do you feel now, living in Tokyo?

500
00:32:01,266 --> 00:32:02,562
Huh? Uh...

501
00:32:02,881 --> 00:32:05,923
I don't feel like I'm suffocating anymore.

502
00:32:06,288 --> 00:32:08,096
Well, that's great, right?

503
00:32:08,346 --> 00:32:09,871
Bon appétit.

504
00:32:15,824 --> 00:32:17,753
Mmm!

505
00:32:19,969 --> 00:32:21,494
Wh-What's that? An earthquake?

506
00:32:21,519 --> 00:32:22,721
No. No.

507
00:32:22,965 --> 00:32:24,736
It's just the train.

508
00:32:27,787 --> 00:32:28,676
Hodaka,

509
00:32:28,701 --> 00:32:29,695
are you serious?

510
00:32:29,925 --> 00:32:30,734
Why not?

511
00:32:30,959 --> 00:32:32,698
I mean, you're a real sunshine girl, right?

512
00:32:32,723 --> 00:32:33,285
Mm-hmm.

513
00:32:33,309 --> 00:32:35,724
You can clear up the sky simply by praying.

514
00:32:35,749 --> 00:32:36,468
I guess.

515
00:32:36,492 --> 00:32:37,647
Then why not?

516
00:32:37,672 --> 00:32:39,141
You said you needed a job, right?

517
00:32:39,220 --> 00:32:42,230
I really do. But I feel weird charging.

518
00:32:42,265 --> 00:32:47,110
Well, would you rather go back to that club? 'Cause
I don't think you're cut out for that kind of work.

519
00:32:47,817 --> 00:32:49,174
Hodaka.

520
00:32:49,636 --> 00:32:50,831
What are you looking at?

521
00:32:50,855 --> 00:32:52,368
I'm not looking at anything!

522
00:32:52,542 --> 00:32:53,679
Sorry.

523
00:32:54,785 --> 00:32:57,128
Isn't 5,000 yen too expensive?

524
00:32:57,180 --> 00:32:59,629
Okay. Uh, how about 3,000?

525
00:32:59,804 --> 00:33:03,363
Hmm, but in order to cover my living expenses...

526
00:33:04,157 --> 00:33:05,294
We should have some artwork.

527
00:33:05,319 --> 00:33:06,669
Oh, I can draw something.

528
00:33:07,625 --> 00:33:08,569
What is that?

529
00:33:09,045 --> 00:33:09,976
A hippo?

530
00:33:10,298 --> 00:33:11,159
It's a frog.

531
00:33:11,452 --> 00:33:13,168
S-Seriously?

532
00:33:13,749 --> 00:33:15,513
It's done!

533
00:33:15,767 --> 00:33:16,927
All right, I'm uploading.

534
00:33:17,014 --> 00:33:17,869
Everything look good?

535
00:33:17,893 --> 00:33:18,468
Yeah.

536
00:33:19,372 --> 00:33:20,526
I'm home.

537
00:33:20,573 --> 00:33:23,076
Hey, the sardines were on sale, so I...

538
00:33:23,212 --> 00:33:23,997
Oh.

539
00:33:25,143 --> 00:33:25,640
Who are you?

540
00:33:25,675 --> 00:33:27,892
Uh, y-you're that kid!

541
00:33:27,987 --> 00:33:29,400
From the back of the bus.

542
00:33:29,425 --> 00:33:29,818
Huh?

543
00:33:29,842 --> 00:33:31,202
You guys know each other?

544
00:33:31,434 --> 00:33:33,120
Hodaka, this is my brother Nagi.

545
00:33:33,250 --> 00:33:34,750
Nagi, this is Hodaka,

546
00:33:34,859 --> 00:33:36,953
my brand-new business partner.

547
00:33:36,977 --> 00:33:37,432
Huh?

548
00:33:38,141 --> 00:33:40,033
Whoa! We've got a response already!

549
00:33:40,071 --> 00:33:41,868
What? You actually uploaded it?

550
00:33:41,955 --> 00:33:44,916
And they say that... that they
want good weather for a flea market.

551
00:33:45,170 --> 00:33:46,450
Uh, and it's tomorrow!

552
00:33:46,601 --> 00:33:47,547
Hang on a minute.

553
00:33:47,674 --> 00:33:49,430
Am I really going to do this?

554
