565
00:34:12,420 --> 00:34:14,184
Uh, th-that's okay.

566
00:34:14,209 --> 00:34:15,592
I have another secret weapon.

567
00:34:23,895 --> 00:34:25,254
Sorry, but no.

568
00:34:25,883 --> 00:34:27,549
I told you, Hodaka!

569
00:34:29,361 --> 00:34:30,981
Who called these guys again?

570
00:34:31,006 --> 00:34:32,944
What a bunch of weirdos.

571
00:34:33,349 --> 00:34:35,748
Uh, we figured it couldn't hurt.

572
00:34:40,382 --> 00:34:42,127
Don't worry about it, kids.

573
00:34:42,152 --> 00:34:43,536
I don't think it's working.

574
00:34:43,561 --> 00:34:45,848
We can do this. We're-we're almost there.

575
00:34:45,895 --> 00:34:47,222
Do you... do you need some water, Hina?

576
00:34:47,257 --> 00:34:49,002
Uh, how about some candy?

577
00:34:49,629 --> 00:34:51,136
Just tell 'em to go home.

578
00:34:51,297 --> 00:34:52,089
Okay.

579
00:34:52,378 --> 00:34:52,861
The sky!

580
00:34:52,896 --> 00:34:53,872
Huh?

581
00:35:06,832 --> 00:35:09,681
It's been forever since I've seen the sun.

582
00:35:11,501 --> 00:35:12,939
It's so pretty.

583
00:35:12,964 --> 00:35:14,536
Huh. Will you look at that?

584
00:35:14,561 --> 00:35:15,737
How'd I do?

585
00:35:15,904 --> 00:35:17,460
That was truly amazing.

586
00:35:17,485 --> 00:35:18,963
You are a sunshine girl.

587
00:35:19,034 --> 00:35:20,833
I can't believe that actually worked.

588
00:35:20,857 --> 00:35:23,769
You kids did great, even if it was a coincidence.

589
00:35:23,794 --> 00:35:24,945
It wasn't!

590
00:35:25,328 --> 00:35:27,200
How does 20,000 yen sound?

591
00:35:27,225 --> 00:35:28,079
It's too much.

592
00:35:28,103 --> 00:35:29,092
It's a bonus.

593
00:35:29,195 --> 00:35:30,632
For a job well done.

594
00:35:31,236 --> 00:35:32,300
Thanks again.

595
00:35:32,335 --> 00:35:35,931
People will come out now, and we'll
be... we'll be able to sell more.

596
00:35:44,624 --> 00:35:46,015
Yeah!

597
00:35:46,054 --> 00:35:46,767
That was amazing, sis!

598
00:35:46,791 --> 00:35:47,111
All right!

599
00:35:47,136 --> 00:35:48,577
I can totally do this!

600
00:35:48,601 --> 00:35:49,056
Yeah!

601
00:35:49,081 --> 00:35:50,844
Let's make some money off of the weather!

602
00:35:50,869 --> 00:35:51,174
Yes!

603
00:35:51,198 --> 00:35:51,838
Yeah!

604
00:36:43,092 --> 00:36:45,870
The human mind works in mysterious ways.

605
00:36:46,117 --> 00:36:50,478
Sometimes, you just need to see the sun
shining in the morning to feel energized.

606
00:36:51,137 --> 00:36:53,586
A blue sky can make you feel happy that you're alive.

607
00:36:54,095 --> 00:36:57,971
It makes you feel more in love with
that someone special by your side.

608
00:36:58,669 --> 00:37:02,224
This is a once-in-a-lifetime event,
and it better be under a blue sky.

609
00:37:02,259 --> 00:37:03,977
