areas and only for a brief amount of time.

615
00:37:20,558 --> 00:37:21,643
But it didn't matter.

616
00:37:21,790 --> 00:37:24,007
The sky would always answer her prayers.

617
00:37:24,159 --> 00:37:28,026
She was 100% a real-life sunshine girl!

618
00:37:43,320 --> 00:37:46,419
It was like the whole city was
putting its best foot forward.

619
00:37:47,792 --> 00:37:49,364
It made me think...

620
00:37:50,104 --> 00:37:52,717
what a wonderful world I was born into.

621
00:37:52,915 --> 00:37:54,843
Here we go. Big smiles.

622
00:37:54,868 --> 00:37:56,845
That's it! Go, go!

623
00:37:57,435 --> 00:37:58,847
Look, there's another one.

624
00:38:03,231 --> 00:38:04,094
Thank you.

625
00:38:04,185 --> 00:38:05,160
Thanks a lot.

626
00:38:05,185 --> 00:38:06,207
Thanks.

627
00:38:06,231 --> 00:38:07,242
Thanks, guys.

628
00:38:07,337 --> 00:38:07,978
Thank you.

629
00:38:08,002 --> 00:38:09,666
Thank you so very much.

630
00:38:09,817 --> 00:38:13,352
It's amazing how a simple thing
like the weather can affect our moods.

631
00:38:13,829 --> 00:38:18,246
That was when I realized for the first time just
how much the human heart is connected to the sky.

632
00:38:23,229 --> 00:38:24,398
All right, I'm off.

633
00:38:26,431 --> 00:38:27,304
Huh?

634
00:38:27,911 --> 00:38:29,012
To where?

635
00:38:29,779 --> 00:38:31,546
Ugh. Five more minutes.

636
00:38:31,581 --> 00:38:33,795
Five more minutes... That's all I'm waiting.

637
