rely on just that for such a huge event?

646
00:38:55,805 --> 00:38:59,796
Well, it's supposed to rain all week
long, so I can't exactly postpone it.

647
00:39:00,288 --> 00:39:01,854
I would say we're in a unique situation.

648
00:39:01,933 --> 00:39:03,275
The door is opening.

649
00:39:03,300 --> 00:39:04,602
May as well rely on luck.

650
00:39:04,761 --> 00:39:05,332
Uh...

651
00:39:31,123 --> 00:39:32,543
Huh?

652
00:39:51,860 --> 00:39:56,769
The Jingu Gaien fireworks will start
promptly at 7:00 p.m. as scheduled.

653
00:40:34,794 --> 00:40:36,977
I think that I'm in love.

654
00:40:37,025 --> 00:40:37,408
Huh?

655
00:40:37,900 --> 00:40:40,346
This job, the sunshine girl.

656
00:40:40,933 --> 00:40:43,682
It's like, for the first time in my life,

657
00:40:43,707 --> 00:40:45,079
I've found a purpose.

658
00:40:45,518 --> 00:40:46,869
And you know what?

659
00:40:47,465 --> 00:40:50,580
That's not not not such a bad thing.

660
00:40:50,953 --> 00:40:53,221
Wait. How-how many "nots" is...

661
00:40:53,400 --> 00:40:54,800
Is it bad or not?

662
00:40:55,578 --> 00:40:57,078
Lighten up a little.

663
00:40:58,366 --> 00:41:01,544
And so, thank you, Hodaka.

664
00:41:07,655 --> 00:41:09,298
Weather is such a mystery.

665
00:41:10,497 --> 00:41:13,905
Seeing a beautiful sky can really make you feel things.

666
00:41:14,389 --> 00:41:15,717
Just like Hina.

667
00:41:17,322 --> 00:41:19,968
She really makes me feel things.

668
00:41:37,482 --> 00:41:42,319
Yesterday's Jingu Gaien fireworks were
blessed with sudden miraculous clear skies.

