That's incredible.

720
00:44:05,790 --> 00:44:07,336
It really cleared up.

721
00:44:08,752 --> 00:44:10,333
You kids are amazing.

722
00:44:10,603 --> 00:44:12,358
It's a shame you're planning to quit.

723
00:44:13,408 --> 00:44:16,458
Since she was caught on camera,
we've been flooded with requests.

724
00:44:16,903 --> 00:44:18,299
We can't handle them all.

725
00:44:18,872 --> 00:44:22,726
We have one more scheduled, so we'll
do that, and then we'll stop for a while.

726
00:44:23,686 --> 00:44:24,767
And besides...

727
00:44:24,934 --> 00:44:26,785
All right, good job, sis.

728
00:44:27,968 --> 00:44:30,082
Hey, Grandma. I see you got people over.

729
00:44:30,217 --> 00:44:31,640
I wasn't expecting you.

730
00:44:31,665 --> 00:44:33,318
Just stopped by to see if you needed help.

731
00:44:33,873 --> 00:44:35,685
You've got some really young guests.

732
00:44:35,955 --> 00:44:37,274
Are you friends of Grandma's?

733
00:44:37,409 --> 00:44:38,212
Hello.

734
00:44:38,815 --> 00:44:41,222
I wanted nice weather for Grandpa's Hatsubon.

735
00:44:41,247 --> 00:44:42,644
Ah. Nice.

736
00:44:42,715 --> 00:44:44,503
Well, it did stop raining.

737
00:44:51,910 --> 00:44:55,301
It'd be hard for him to come back
with all the rain we've been having.

738
00:44:56,118 --> 00:44:56,783
"Come back"?

739
00:44:56,945 --> 00:44:57,971
The Obon,

740
00:44:58,040 --> 00:45:00,885
the day the dead come back from the sky to visit.

741
00:45:01,607 --> 00:45:02,704
His first Obon?

742
00:45:02,831 --> 00:45:05,216
So, then your grandpa died about a year ago?

743
00:45:05,501 --> 00:45:06,343
That's right.

744
00:45:07,267 --> 00:45:09,169
Yeah, same goes for my mom, too.

745
00:45:10,444 --> 00:45:13,732
Oh, did you lose your mother this past year, sweetie?

746
00:45:13,812 --> 00:45:14,980
Uh, yes.

747
00:45:15,472 --> 00:45:18,529
Then let's light a welcoming fire for her as well.

748
00:45:18,821 --> 00:45:20,613
I know she's watching over you.

749
00:45:21,235 --> 00:45:22,192
Thanks.

750
00:45:26,880 --> 00:45:30,422
The spirits follow the smoke,
and that's how they come back.

751
00:45:31,479 --> 00:45:32,583
Back from where?

752
00:45:32,769 --> 00:45:33,950
From Heaven.

753
00:45:34,952 --> 00:45:38,367
There's always been another world up there in the sky.

754
00:45:43,805 --> 00:45:47,847
This painting is apparently
of what the Weather Maiden saw.

755
00:45:48,347 --> 00:45:50,699
It sure is mysterious.

756
00:45:50,779 --> 00:45:53,019
I mean, there's a flying fish and a dragon?

757
00:45:53,044 --> 00:45:54,569
Absolutely stunning.

758
00:45:54,672 --> 00:45:56,157
Isn't it, though?

759
00:45:56,396 --> 00:45:58,526
So, this Weather Maiden, what is she?

760
00:45:58,637 --> 00:46:00,282
Like a shaman or what?

761
00:46:00,917 --> 00:46:01,578
Huh? What?

762
00:46:01,617 --> 00:46:02,641
Oh, he...

763
00:46:02,697 --> 00:46:04,834
Is the Weather Maiden like a shaman?

764
00:46:05,868 --> 00:46:06,931
Uh-huh.

765
00:46:08,020 --> 00:46:12,214
Mending the ailing weather is
the charge of the Weather Maiden.

766
00:46:12,714 --> 00:46:14,353
So, is it like her job?

767
00:46:14,385 --> 00:46:15,393
Sounds like a scam.

768
00:46:15,448 --> 00:46:19,030
Does that mean she could fix
the abnormal weather we're having?

769
00:46:19,145 --> 00:46:22,598
Huh? There's nothing abnormal about the rain.

770
00:46:22,915 --> 00:46:25,722
The news makes a big deal about everything.

771
00:46:25,920 --> 00:46:28,358
They always say things like "record-breaking,"

772
00:46:28,874 --> 00:46:31,170
but when did their records start?

773
00:46:31,321 --> 00:46:33,029
100 years ago?

774
00:46:33,434 --> 00:46:35,827
How old do you think this painting is?

775
00:46:36,303 --> 00:46:37,950
800 years old, at least.

776
00:46:37,975 --> 00:46:39,005
800?

777
00:46:39,563 --> 00:46:42,247
Hey, you're getting yourself all worked up.

778
00:46:42,310 --> 00:46:44,726
Oh, oh, is he...?

779
00:46:45,138 --> 00:46:48,746
My point is the weather can suddenly change on a whim,

780
00:46:48,873 --> 00:46:51,168
regardless of our human needs.

781
00:46:51,240 --> 00:46:54,887
So we cannot tell what is normal and what is not.

782
00:46:55,085 --> 00:46:58,995
We merely have been allowed to stay in this shifting space

783
00:46:59,020 --> 00:47:02,531
between the heavens and earth, clinging for our lives,

784
00:47:02,634 --> 00:47:05,747
trying our best not to be shaken off.

785
00:47:05,921 --> 00:47:10,330
This is something we humans were
much more aware of in the past.

786
00:47:10,792 --> 00:47:16,080
However, there's a thin thread
binding us humans to the sky.

787
00:47:17,433 --> 00:47:19,713
And that is the Weather Maiden.

788
00:47:20,316 --> 00:47:24,846
A special girl with the ability
to gather the people's wishes

789
00:47:24,881 --> 00:47:27,509
and deliver them to the heavens.

790
00:47:27,917 --> 00:47:33,578
In ancient times, there was one
in every village in every country.

791
00:47:33,626 --> 00:47:35,293
Hey, Kei. Sound like anyone you know?

792
00:47:35,318 --> 00:47:39,250
You know, you don't have to
listen to everything Grandpa says.

793
00:47:39,275 --> 00:47:41,252
No one actually believes in that stuff.

794
00:47:42,278 --> 00:47:43,508
No, no, I love it.

795
00:47:43,635 --> 00:47:45,648
We're grateful for all of your insight.

796
00:47:45,797 --> 00:47:47,372
Just remember, though,

797
00:47:47,698 --> 00:47:50,691
everything comes with a price.

798
00:47:51,332 --> 00:47:53,179
This is no exception.

799
00:47:53,377 --> 00:47:56,411
A tragic fate awaits the Weather Maiden.

800
00:47:59,312 --> 00:48:01,735
One, two, three.

801
00:48:02,108 --> 00:48:03,943
All right, it's your turn, sis.

802
00:48:05,189 --> 00:48:06,461
One, two, three.

803
00:48:06,660 --> 00:48:08,313
Thanks for keeping Grandma company.

804
00:48:08,338 --> 00:48:09,510
- It's really kind of you.

805
00:48:09,537 --> 00:48:11,937
Oh, we're actually here 'cause she hired us.

806
00:48:11,961 --> 00:48:13,462
You have to. Come on.

807
00:48:13,747 --> 00:48:15,503
Well, they're having fun.

808
00:48:16,313 --> 00:48:17,593
How old are you guys, anyway?

809
00:48:17,751 --> 00:48:20,483
