Hey, wait. I said wait!

817
00:48:49,126 --> 00:48:50,421
Just great.

818
00:48:54,982 --> 00:48:56,944
Ah, what the hell?

819
00:48:59,184 --> 00:49:00,630
I said wait!

820
00:49:14,789 --> 00:49:17,020
Whoa, guys. You got to cut me some slack.

821
00:49:17,258 --> 00:49:19,323
I didn't know she was a minor. I swear.

822
00:49:21,307 --> 00:49:23,597
Huh? Wait, so this isn't about the girl?

823
00:49:23,632 --> 00:49:25,270
That's what we've been trying to tell you.

824
00:49:26,066 --> 00:49:27,980
You made us run for nothing.

825
00:49:28,170 --> 00:49:29,875
This is you, is it not?

826
00:49:29,899 --> 00:49:30,490
What?

827
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:33,151
Take a good look.

828
00:49:33,376 --> 00:49:35,732
What do you know about the boy in the video?

829
00:49:38,800 --> 00:49:41,302
So, the kid's about high-school age, huh?

830
00:49:41,850 --> 00:49:45,370
Maybe he picked up the gun
Shibata threw away by pure accident.

831
00:49:46,594 --> 00:49:49,795
If that's the case, then the
kid might have posted about it.

832
00:49:51,360 --> 00:49:53,218
Oh. You mean online.

833
00:49:54,181 --> 00:49:55,674
Yeah, nothing is private.

834
00:49:55,699 --> 00:49:58,177
Kids post everything on social media these days.

835
00:50:14,933 --> 00:50:17,355
Go, Nagi, go!

836
00:50:17,720 --> 00:50:18,269
Yeah!

837
00:50:18,294 --> 00:50:19,198
That was amazing, Nagi!

838
00:50:19,223 --> 00:50:20,254
Yeah! Great shot!

839
00:50:23,903 --> 00:50:25,939
A ring. Definitely a ring.

840
00:50:26,312 --> 00:50:28,829
What? You sure it's not too much?

841
00:50:28,892 --> 00:50:31,236
We're talking about my sister's birthday, right?

842
00:50:32,238 --> 00:50:34,486
I did ask a woman for ideas, but...

843
00:50:34,517 --> 00:50:35,899
I know what I'd like.

844
00:50:36,034 --> 00:50:37,948
Hugs and kisses, money,

845
00:50:38,148 --> 00:50:40,500
boyfriend and a real job.

846
00:50:40,611 --> 00:50:42,660
But she wasn't very helpful.

847
00:50:43,670 --> 00:50:45,079
See you later, Nagi.

848
00:50:45,353 --> 00:50:46,711
See you around, Nagi.

849
00:50:46,948 --> 00:50:47,715
Mm-hmm.

850
00:50:48,007 --> 00:50:50,716
Just admit it. You're in love with my sister.

851
00:50:50,851 --> 00:50:51,447
Huh?

852
00:50:52,376 --> 00:50:54,069
No, it's-it's noth-nothing like that.

853
00:50:54,094 --> 00:50:56,135
Uh, oh, wait. What if it is? Then what?

854
00:50:56,175 --> 00:50:57,272
You know...

855
00:50:57,297 --> 00:50:59,859
Being ambivalent is the worst thing as a man.

856
00:50:59,899 --> 00:51:01,450
Uh, is that true?

857
00:51:01,475 --> 00:51:03,659
Be clear before you start going out.

858
00:51:03,778 --> 00:51:06,297
Then you can be vague. Those are the basics.

859
00:51:08,434 --> 00:51:10,611
I should call you "Sempai."

860
00:51:13,256 --> 00:51:14,899
Ever since our mom died,

861
00:51:14,924 --> 00:51:16,831
my sister's been working nonstop.

862
00:51:17,173 --> 00:51:19,713
I know the reason she's doing it is for me.

863
00:51:19,786 --> 00:51:21,073
'Cause I'm still a kid.

864
00:51:22,599 --> 00:51:24,378
So that's why

865
00:51:24,839 --> 00:51:26,937
I want to see her get to do more teenage stuff.

866
00:51:27,317 --> 00:51:30,153
But you're gonna have to prove
you're the guy for the job, okay?

867
00:51:32,388 --> 00:51:34,247
Here you go. Enjoy.

868
00:51:37,391 --> 00:51:38,266
Thank you.

869
00:51:38,655 --> 00:51:39,333
But, uh...

870
00:51:39,784 --> 00:51:41,230
do you think she'll like it?

871
00:51:41,508 --> 00:51:42,216
Huh?

872
00:51:43,763 --> 00:51:44,750
Don't worry.

873
00:51:44,877 --> 00:51:46,942
We spent three hours picking it out.

874
00:51:47,180 --> 00:51:49,460
If it were me, I'd be very happy.

875
00:51:50,079 --> 00:51:51,930
Good luck, okay?

876
00:51:56,897 --> 00:51:59,296
Tomorrow's sunshine girl job will be our last.

877
00:52:00,243 --> 00:52:04,387
Our customer is a man who requested good weather
at the park so that he could play with his daughter.

878
00:52:06,279 --> 00:52:07,574
After that appointment,

879
00:52:08,573 --> 00:52:10,378
I plan on giving Hina the ring.

880
00:52:21,734 --> 00:52:24,696
Daddy, can you do it one more time?

881
00:52:25,109 --> 00:52:27,414
Okay. Are you ready?

882
00:52:32,817 --> 00:52:34,017
Oh, man.

883
00:52:34,335 --> 00:52:35,948
That was tough on my back.

884
00:52:36,187 --> 00:52:38,283
Of all the people that could have hired us.

885
00:52:38,363 --> 00:52:40,547
Did you already know I was doing this as a side job, huh?

886
00:52:40,626 --> 00:52:44,263
I bet you knew this entire time and said
nothing. And since when have you had a daughter?!

887
00:52:45,328 --> 00:52:46,624
Well, I'm impressed.

888
00:52:46,719 --> 00:52:49,253
The forecast said it'd be 100% rain today.

889
00:52:50,326 --> 00:52:53,416
Yeah, unfortunately, my daughter has asthma.

890
00:52:53,987 --> 00:52:58,008
And she lives with her grandmother, who
won't let me see her if it's raining out, so...

891
00:52:58,214 --> 00:52:59,652
it's been tough lately.

892
00:53:00,869 --> 00:53:04,086
There's nothing more gorgeous than a beautiful, clear sky.

893
00:53:04,111 --> 00:53:04,953
I concur.

894
00:53:05,176 --> 00:53:06,698
I take it you're Hodaka's boss, then?

895
00:53:06,788 --> 00:53:09,083
Yep. I also saved his life.

896
00:53:09,575 --> 00:53:11,525
Hey, does your friend always speak so formally?

897
00:53:11,550 --> 00:53:14,471
Huh? Well, Hina is a whole two years older than me.

898
00:53:14,534 --> 00:53:15,840
What? Ridiculous.

899
00:53:15,925 --> 00:53:18,108
16, 17, 18... There's no difference.

900
00:53:18,133 --> 00:53:18,900
Yeah, there is!

901
00:53:18,924 --> 00:53:19,619
Yeah, you're right.

902
00:53:19,644 --> 00:53:20,701
Ugh! There you are.

903
00:53:20,843 --> 00:53:22,184
Hey!

904
00:53:22,278 --> 00:53:23,432
Did I miss anything?

905
00:53:23,646 --> 00:53:25,575
Wh-What are you gonna do about her?

906
00:53:25,600 --> 00:53:26,782
Aren't you gonna be in trouble?

907
00:53:26,890 --> 00:53:27,420
Hmm?

908
00:53:27,666 --> 00:53:30,114
I mean, does Natsumi even know that you're married?

909
00:53:30,606 --> 00:53:32,760
What's wrong? You okay?

910
00:53:36,145 --> 00:53:39,411
Hodaka, he... he actually thought you were my...

911
00:53:39,570 --> 00:53:41,419
Mistress?!

912
00:53:42,540 --> 00:53:45,328
Hang on. You never mentioned that she's your niece.

913
00:53:45,353 --> 00:53:48,164
So, this whole time, you had disgusting fantasies?

914
00:53:48,189 --> 00:53:49,412
That is so perverted.

915
00:53:50,142 --> 00:53:52,288
Classic Hodaka.

916
00:53:54,774 --> 00:53:55,970
Hmm.

917
00:53:56,196 --> 00:53:57,357
Are you looking at my boobs?

918
00:53:57,382 --> 00:53:58,317
I am not!

919
00:53:59,351 --> 00:54:00,717
Natsumi!

920
00:54:00,742 --> 00:54:02,643
Hey, Moka. What do you got there?

921
00:54:02,678 --> 00:54:04,842
Daddy, look! A flower crown.

922
00:54:04,913 --> 00:54:05,649
I made it for you!

923
00:54:05,673 --> 00:54:06,947
Yeah? Let me see.

924
00:54:07,145 --> 00:54:08,527
Hodaka, join us.

925
00:54:08,552 --> 00:54:10,432
Uh, Sempai calls.

926
00:54:13,063 --> 00:54:14,613
Hodaka is such a riot.

927
00:54:14,716 --> 00:54:16,130
He is such a child.

928
00:54:16,505 --> 00:54:19,602
They're like the older and younger
versions of each other, don't you think?

929
00:54:20,040 --> 00:54:21,291
Hodaka and Mr. Suga?

930
00:54:21,315 --> 00:54:22,064
Yeah.

931
00:54:22,183 --> 00:54:25,679
Kei ran away from home and came to
Tokyo when he was a teenager, too.

932
00:54:25,830 --> 00:54:28,722
Then he met and fell madly in love with his future wife.

933
00:54:29,908 --> 00:54:32,965
But then, a few years ago, she died in an accident.

934
00:54:33,342 --> 00:54:35,543
He's still very much in love with her, though.

935
00:54:37,478 --> 00:54:38,390
It's so good to meet you.

936
00:54:38,414 --> 00:54:40,465
I've been wanting to for a long time.

937
00:54:41,005 --> 00:54:43,620
You're the real sunshine girl. That's amazing!

938
00:54:43,698 --> 00:54:46,764
I wish I had a special skill
to put on my résumé like that.

939
00:54:46,789 --> 00:54:49,325
I hate looking for a job. Too bad I'm not in high school.

940
00:54:50,547 --> 00:54:51,412
It's funny.

941
00:54:52,113 --> 00:54:54,511
'Cause for me, I can't wait to grow up.

942
00:54:54,854 --> 00:54:55,671
Huh.

943
00:54:56,331 --> 00:54:58,399
Yeah, I understand that.

944
00:54:58,587 --> 00:54:59,983
I'm glad you're
doing well, though.

945
00:55:00,008 --> 00:55:00,467
Huh?

946
00:55:01,023 --> 00:55:02,916
Actually, I was a bit worried about you.

947
00:55:03,551 --> 00:55:04,237
Huh?

948
00:55:12,350 --> 00:55:14,381
You okay, Moka? You tired?

949
00:55:14,416 --> 00:55:15,486
Here you go.

950
00:55:15,754 --> 00:55:17,940
One, two, three.

951
00:55:19,673 --> 00:55:21,991
I'm fine. I want to keep playing.

952
00:55:22,016 --> 00:55:23,390
I know, but it's raining.

953
00:55:23,415 --> 00:55:25,625
We're taking off. Have a good day, okay?

954
00:55:26,109 --> 00:55:29,258
But I want to hang out with Nagi some more.

955
00:55:29,283 --> 00:55:31,069
Then why don't we all grab some dinner?

956
00:55:31,094 --> 00:55:32,421
I'm sorry, but...

957
00:55:32,446 --> 00:55:34,412
Hey, how about I just go eat with Moka, then?

958
00:55:34,462 --> 00:55:35,408
Would that be okay?

959
00:55:35,606 --> 00:55:36,157
Great.

960
00:55:36,217 --> 00:55:37,371
Yay!

961
00:55:37,775 --> 00:55:39,498
Hodaka, can you take Hina home?

962
00:55:39,554 --> 00:55:40,109
Uh...

963
00:55:41,198 --> 00:55:42,208
Hey, whoa, uh...

964
00:55:44,187 --> 00:55:47,490
Hina, thank you for bringing the sunshine today.

965
00:55:49,009 --> 00:55:50,184
Thank you.

966
00:55:50,501 --> 00:55:52,086
I'm happy you're happy.

967
00:56:07,664 --> 00:56:08,719
Oh, my God.

968
00:56:09,705 --> 00:56:11,834
Oh, my God. Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

969
00:56:12,088 --> 00:56:13,407
This might be...

970
00:56:14,177 --> 00:56:15,639
the very first time that...

971
00:56:16,695 --> 00:56:18,601
I tell someone I love them.

972
00:56:28,980 --> 00:56:29,744
Hina, I...!

973
00:56:29,769 --> 00:56:30,101
Hodaka.

974
00:56:30,197 --> 00:56:30,876
Oh, sorry.

975
00:56:30,900 --> 00:56:31,404
Uh...

976
00:56:32,467 --> 00:56:33,307
What is it?

977
00:56:33,331 --> 00:56:34,561
Nothing in particular.

978
00:56:34,907 --> 00:56:36,399
What did you want to say?

979
00:56:40,411 --> 00:56:41,533
Hodaka,

980
00:56:41,975 --> 00:56:43,692
so, um...

981
00:56:46,479 --> 00:56:47,511
I...

982
00:56:58,230 --> 00:56:59,111
Hina!

983
00:57:04,992 --> 00:57:05,849
Hodaka!

984
00:57:06,159 --> 00:57:07,621
Where are you, Hina?

985
00:57:36,644 --> 00:57:38,605
I think I know when I became

986
00:57:38,695 --> 00:57:39,861
a sunshine girl.

987
00:57:41,165 --> 00:57:45,335
It was one year ago, on that day.

988
00:57:51,154 --> 00:57:54,218
I spent the entire day before praying for good weather.

989
00:57:55,710 --> 00:57:58,897
I wanted to have one last walk under the sun with my mom.

990
00:58:05,389 --> 00:58:06,796
And then I saw it.

991
00:58:07,312 --> 00:58:09,123
It looked like a pool of light.

992
00:58:09,504 --> 00:58:13,882
And praying with all my heart, I crossed the shrine gate.

993
00:58:25,862 --> 00:58:29,971
When I finally came to, I was lying on the ground,

994
00:58:30,535 --> 00:58:32,434
and the sky was clear.

995
00:58:39,798 --> 00:58:41,665
I think that's when it happened.

996
00:58:42,094 --> 00:58:43,047
That's when...

997
00:58:43,317 --> 00:58:45,573
I became connected to the sky.

998
00:58:51,591 --> 00:58:54,417
Is it true? Connected to the sky?

999
00:58:56,380 --> 00:58:58,961
Hodaka, don't come out.

1000
00:59:01,836 --> 00:59:04,459
It's the police. Sorry for the late visit.

1001
00:59:04,546 --> 00:59:05,452
The police?

1002
00:59:05,993 --> 00:59:06,780
Look again.

1003
00:59:06,805 --> 00:59:08,479
You sure you haven't seen him before?

1004
00:59:09,574 --> 00:59:13,404
Someone fitting his description has
been reported several times in this area.

1005
00:59:13,777 --> 00:59:14,931
I don't know him.

1006
00:59:15,343 --> 00:59:17,051
May I ask what he's done?

1007
00:59:17,440 --> 00:59:19,991
We just want to ask him some questions. That's all.

1008
00:59:20,134 --> 00:59:21,828
He's a minor and a runaway.

1009
00:59:22,136 --> 00:59:25,198
Additionally, his parents have
filed a missing persons report.

1010
00:59:26,166 --> 00:59:29,827
We've also been told that you live
here on your own with your little brother.

1011
00:59:29,867 --> 00:59:30,988
Is that correct?

1012
00:59:31,535 --> 00:59:32,243
Yes.

1013
00:59:32,386 --> 00:59:34,666
That, unfortunately, is another issue.

1014
00:59:35,287 --> 00:59:37,963
Children cannot live on their own without a guardian.

1015
00:59:37,988 --> 00:59:38,568
But...!

1016
00:59:38,956 --> 00:59:39,718
Sorry.

1017
00:59:39,978 --> 00:59:42,420
But we're quiet and don't cause trouble.

1018
00:59:45,479 --> 00:59:46,027
Hina.

1019
00:59:46,805 --> 00:59:49,761
She said that she was going to come back tomorrow,

1020
00:59:49,817 --> 00:59:51,224
bring child services.

1021
00:59:51,374 --> 00:59:52,693
What do I do?

1022
00:59:52,733 --> 00:59:54,322
They're going to separate us.

1023
00:59:54,370 --> 00:59:55,657
I just know it.

1024
01:00:07,871 --> 01:00:09,843
Hodaka, the police.

1025
01:00:09,878 --> 01:00:10,763
They were just...

1026
01:00:11,291 --> 01:00:11,899
I know.

1027
01:00:12,018 --> 01:00:13,742
Go inside. I'll be back tomorrow.

1028
01:00:16,563 --> 01:00:17,705
Mr. Suga?

1029
01:00:18,412 --> 01:00:20,224
Hey. Like the new look?

1030
01:00:20,568 --> 01:00:22,371
I'm in disguise.

1031
01:00:22,997 --> 01:00:25,698
Earlier today, the police stopped by my office.

1032
01:00:26,238 --> 01:00:28,502
They're treating your disappearance as a kidnapping.

1033
01:00:29,169 --> 01:00:32,729
I denied any involvement, but I
can tell they still suspect me.

1034
01:00:33,436 --> 01:00:35,518
Consider this your severance pay.

1035
01:00:35,577 --> 01:00:35,986
Huh?

1036
01:00:36,494 --> 01:00:40,235
I can't have you coming back to the office.
If they catch you there, they'll arrest me.

1037
01:00:44,266 --> 01:00:47,332
I'm in the process of filing for custody of my daughter,

1038
01:00:47,444 --> 01:00:49,755
so I got to be careful, understand?

1039
01:00:50,461 --> 01:00:53,242
If I were you, I'd head back home tomorrow.

1040
01:00:53,472 --> 01:00:56,023
Then everything can go back to normal.

1041
01:00:56,452 --> 01:00:57,883
It'll be best for everyone.

1042
01:00:58,112 --> 01:00:59,455
You'll see.

1043
01:01:01,601 --> 01:01:04,142
Time to grow up, little man. Got it?

1044
01:01:13,821 --> 01:01:15,408
We can't stay here anymore.

1045
01:01:15,781 --> 01:01:17,761
But... where will you go?

1046
01:01:17,786 --> 01:01:19,564
I don't know, but...

1047
01:01:20,835 --> 01:01:24,037
Hey, it doesn't matter where
we go, as long as we're together.

1048
01:01:24,236 --> 01:01:28,789
Hmm. Hodaka, you should probably go
home before you get caught by the police.

1049
01:01:29,297 --> 01:01:31,306
At least you've got a place to go back to.

1050
01:01:31,885 --> 01:01:32,798
Don't say that.

1051
01:01:35,437 --> 01:01:37,351
Don't worry. We're gonna be fine.

1052
01:01:38,972 --> 01:01:39,750
No way.

1053
01:01:40,265 --> 01:01:41,450
I'm not going back.

1054
01:01:42,689 --> 01:01:43,882
Let's run away!

1055
01:01:49,923 --> 01:01:54,639
A special heavy rain advisory has
just been issued in the Tokyo area.

1056
01:01:54,828 --> 01:01:56,047
It could be the heaviest downpour

1057
01:01:56,072 --> 01:01:58,218
that the city has experienced in decades.

1058
01:01:58,253 --> 01:02:01,084
Lowland communities should be prepared for flash flooding.

1059
01:02:01,109 --> 01:02:03,720
A sudden typhoon-strength low-pressure system is...

1060
01:02:04,204 --> 01:02:05,635
River levels rising.

1061
01:02:05,881 --> 01:02:07,644
Increased risk of flooding.

1062
01:02:07,979 --> 01:02:09,853
The dam is not going to hold!

1063
01:02:09,878 --> 01:02:12,539
Keep calm and slowly make your way towards the exit.

1064
01:02:12,730 --> 01:02:16,803
The Namboku Line at Akabane-Iwabuchi
Station, the Shibuya Metro...

1065
01:02:16,828 --> 01:02:19,762
Outgoing flights have been canceled from Haneda Airport.

1066
01:02:19,850 --> 01:02:23,735
Over six inches of rain is falling per hour, and
heavy flooding has been reported in many areas in Tokyo.

1067
01:02:23,760 --> 01:02:25,056
Sir, are you okay?

1068
01:02:25,212 --> 01:02:27,158
Kita Ward, Arakawa Ward,

1069
01:02:27,269 --> 01:02:29,526
Taito Ward, Sumida Ward, Shibuya...

1070
01:02:29,573 --> 01:02:31,924
Please head home immediately.

1071
01:02:32,053 --> 01:02:34,023
It's really cold, right?

1072
01:02:34,048 --> 01:02:36,089
It has been a record-breaking August.

1073
01:02:36,124 --> 01:02:39,138
The temperature in Tokyo has fallen below 50 degrees.

1074
01:02:39,163 --> 01:02:40,688
Cumulonimbi continue to gather above Tokyo.

1075
01:02:40,713 --> 01:02:42,111
In merely an hour,

1076
01:02:42,143 --> 01:02:43,979
Tokyo's landscape has been transformed.

1077
01:02:44,169 --> 01:02:47,912
I repeat, a heavy rain special advisory
has been issued for the greater Tokyo area.

1078
01:02:47,966 --> 01:02:49,539
This is looking to be the heaviest rainfall

1079
01:02:49,564 --> 01:02:50,982
recorded in the last few decades.

1080
01:02:51,006 --> 01:02:51,994
A low-pressure system over the Kanto region...

1081
01:02:52,019 --> 01:02:56,709
The stream of cold air that passed over
Kanto on the 21st is the cause of the current...

1082
01:02:56,733 --> 01:02:59,096
Active rainclouds will remain over
east and central Japan at least...

1083
01:02:59,121 --> 01:03:02,172
The Meteorological Agency has
stated that this abnormal weather

1084
01:03:02,197 --> 01:03:03,214
will continue for at least the next few weeks.

1085
01:03:03,239 --> 01:03:08,582
Experts warn that the current weather pattern we
are seeing is unprecedented and extremely dangerous.

1086
01:03:14,710 --> 01:03:18,775
Trains on the Yamanote Line are
indefinitely delayed due to the heavy rains.

1087
01:03:19,050 --> 01:03:22,482
There is no way to resume
operations until the weather clears up.

1088
01:03:22,625 --> 01:03:23,554
Let's just get off here.

1089
01:03:23,579 --> 01:03:25,515
Oh, I'll ask my mom to pick us up.

1090
01:03:25,540 --> 01:03:26,622
It's freezing.

1091
01:03:26,741 --> 01:03:27,790
What should we do?

1092
01:03:27,922 --> 01:03:29,126
Hey, don't worry.

1093
01:03:29,475 --> 01:03:31,501
Let's find a place to stay tonight.

1094
01:03:32,605 --> 01:03:35,074
I'm sorry, but we don't have anything available.

1095
01:03:35,122 --> 01:03:36,084
We're fully booked.

1096
01:03:36,140 --> 01:03:37,657
Do you have a reservation?

1097
01:03:37,776 --> 01:03:38,873
We're all full.

1098
01:03:39,125 --> 01:03:40,923
There's no adult with you?

1099
01:03:41,185 --> 01:03:43,306
One last thing... I need to see your I.D.

1100
01:03:43,377 --> 01:03:45,101
We can't accept unaccompanied minors.

1101
01:03:45,370 --> 01:03:46,984
This ain't about the money.

1102
01:03:47,087 --> 01:03:48,668
It's not about the money!

1103
01:03:50,408 --> 01:03:51,417
Be honest.

1104
01:03:51,942 --> 01:03:53,665
Are you kids runaways?

1105
01:04:02,296 --> 01:04:04,439
Hina, Hodaka, look.

1106
01:04:05,536 --> 01:04:07,450
Is that snow?

1107
01:05:01,594 --> 01:05:02,904
Could it be true?

1108
01:05:04,262 --> 01:05:06,621
That Hina is connected to the sky?

1109
01:05:18,692 --> 01:05:20,232
It's freezing.

1110
01:05:21,615 --> 01:05:24,424
Hey, Kei, it's snowing in August.

1111
01:05:24,856 --> 01:05:27,239
It's official... The world's gone crazy.

1112
01:05:27,509 --> 01:05:28,061
Hmm?

1113
01:05:29,064 --> 01:05:29,606
Oh.

1114
01:05:30,330 --> 01:05:33,644
It is difficult to believe,
but it is snowing here in Tokyo.

1115
01:05:33,763 --> 01:05:36,273
Kei, wake up. Hey, you'll catch a cold.

1116
01:05:37,622 --> 01:05:38,325
Asuka.

1117
01:05:41,611 --> 01:05:42,375
Asuka.

1118
01:05:42,787 --> 01:05:44,733
Kei, you, too. Smile!

1119
01:05:50,397 --> 01:05:51,627
Oh, it's cold.

1120
01:05:51,843 --> 01:05:54,465
Careful. You're starting to act like an old man.

1121
01:05:54,490 --> 01:05:56,611
That's what happens when you're old.

1122
01:05:59,321 --> 01:06:03,143
You have to make tough choices 'cause
you've got different priorities, you know.

1123
01:06:03,454 --> 01:06:04,998
What are you saying?

1124
01:06:05,145 --> 01:06:06,369
Where's Hodaka?

1125
01:06:06,576 --> 01:06:08,117
You kicked him out?!

1126
01:06:08,220 --> 01:06:09,634
I don't believe you.

1127
01:06:09,888 --> 01:06:11,692
I told you, the police showed up.

1128
01:06:12,057 --> 01:06:14,687
I've got to protect myself, not some stranger.

1129
01:06:14,901 --> 01:06:18,896
What? And how are you protecting
yourself by smoking and drinking again?

1130
01:06:19,531 --> 01:06:21,390
Not cool. Meow.

1131
01:06:21,852 --> 01:06:23,926
See? Even Rain's judging you.

1132
01:06:24,076 --> 01:06:26,787
Not only is it uncool; it's so last century.

1133
01:06:26,826 --> 01:06:28,955
Don't get near me. I don't want you to rub off on me.

1134
01:06:28,980 --> 01:06:31,728
Ah, you're not exactly cool, either.

1135
01:06:31,855 --> 01:06:33,293
What's her name... Hina?

1136
01:06:33,333 --> 01:06:35,884
If the story about the Weather Maiden is true,

1137
01:06:36,701 --> 01:06:39,362
that she's a human sacrifice, then one day she'll...

1138
01:06:39,387 --> 01:06:40,700
I know, but then...

1139
01:06:41,183 --> 01:06:42,700
what was I supposed to do?

1140
01:06:42,907 --> 01:06:44,704
Ah, come on, relax.

1141
01:06:44,758 --> 01:06:46,434
It's all bullshit anyway.

1142
01:06:47,681 --> 01:06:49,706
Besides, if it were true...

1143
01:06:54,357 --> 01:06:59,572
if you could fix this crazy weather with
one human sacrifice, I'd be fine with it.

1144
01:07:00,747 --> 01:07:02,011
Everyone would.

1145
01:07:03,802 --> 01:07:09,295
A heavy rain and heavy snow advisory has
been issued for Tokyo and its surrounding areas.

1146
01:07:09,767 --> 01:07:13,763
Residents are urged to stay
indoors at all times if possible.

1147
01:07:13,866 --> 01:07:15,464
You kids, hold up.

1148
01:07:16,091 --> 01:07:18,824
It's dangerous to walk around right now unsupervised.

1149
01:07:19,007 --> 01:07:19,950
What are you doing out?

1150
01:07:19,975 --> 01:07:20,880
These your siblings?

1151
01:07:20,905 --> 01:07:21,765
I... Yeah, we're, uh...

1152
01:07:21,790 --> 01:07:23,537
We're actually on our way home.

1153
01:07:23,650 --> 01:07:26,428
I-I'm a college student, and
these are my younger brothers.

1154
01:07:26,453 --> 01:07:28,495
Hmm. I understand, but...

1155
01:07:29,138 --> 01:07:30,650
I'm gonna need to see some I.D.

1156
01:07:30,766 --> 01:07:33,053
Oh, I, uh, don't have it on me.

1157
01:07:33,078 --> 01:07:34,724
We may have located the boy.

1158
01:07:34,749 --> 01:07:37,845
We think he might be carrying
a firearm. Proceed with caution.

1159
01:07:38,814 --> 01:07:40,761
And you... you in high school?

1160
01:07:41,118 --> 01:07:43,063
That's a pretty big backpack you got there.

1161
01:07:43,088 --> 01:07:45,321
Can you remove your hood for us, please?

1162
01:07:46,879 --> 01:07:47,410
Hina.

1163
01:07:47,633 --> 01:07:48,134
Huh?

1164
01:07:48,626 --> 01:07:49,691
Run for it!

1165
01:07:51,407 --> 01:07:52,433
Hey, wait!

1166
01:07:53,179 --> 01:07:54,053
Stop!

1167
01:07:56,469 --> 01:07:57,197
Gotcha!

1168
01:07:57,221 --> 01:07:58,351
Let go of me!

1169
01:07:59,065 --> 01:08:00,425
Will you settle down?!

1170
01:08:04,594 --> 01:08:05,479
Get off!

1171
01:08:05,503 --> 01:08:06,363
Stop struggling.

1172
01:08:07,311 --> 01:08:07,936
Stop it! No!

1173
01:08:07,960 --> 01:08:08,521
Hodaka!

1174
01:08:08,820 --> 01:08:09,646
No!

1175
01:08:10,352 --> 01:08:11,878
Stay where you are!

1176
01:08:14,464 --> 01:08:15,309
Hina.

1177
01:08:15,853 --> 01:08:18,028
Please!

1178
01:08:33,521 --> 01:08:34,617
Clear the area!

1179
01:08:39,569 --> 01:08:41,402
Hina, we've got to go.

1180
01:08:41,427 --> 01:08:42,954
Let's go take a closer look.

1181
01:08:43,892 --> 01:08:44,755
Come on.

1182
01:08:54,195 --> 01:08:55,776
It's 280 a night.

1183
01:08:56,263 --> 01:08:56,802
Uh...

1184
01:08:57,223 --> 01:08:58,929
So, can you pay it? 280.

1185
01:08:58,954 --> 01:09:01,027
Oh, y... oh, yes, uh, of course I can.

1186
01:09:11,228 --> 01:09:12,387
It's official.

1187
01:09:12,554 --> 01:09:14,802
Looks like I'm a full-fledged fugitive now.

1188
01:09:14,913 --> 01:09:16,168
That's so cool.

1189
01:09:16,482 --> 01:09:16,819
Huh?

1190
01:09:20,555 --> 01:09:22,643
That almost gave me a heart attack.

1191
01:09:22,753 --> 01:09:23,692
You totally almost got arrested.

1192
01:09:23,734 --> 01:09:25,189
Why are you laughing?

1193
01:09:25,213 --> 01:09:26,203
'Cause it was funny.

1194
01:09:26,228 --> 01:09:28,201
I'm glad you think so.

1195
01:09:28,254 --> 01:09:29,182
It's huge.

1196
01:09:29,470 --> 01:09:30,692
The bed's huge.

1197
01:09:30,803 --> 01:09:32,145
The bathtub's huge.

1198
01:09:33,585 --> 01:09:34,736
Whoa.

1199
01:09:35,149 --> 01:09:36,853
Hina. Hodaka.

1200
01:09:37,008 --> 01:09:38,187
Let's take a bath together.

1201
01:09:39,178 --> 01:09:40,528
Take it by yourself!

1202
01:09:40,816 --> 01:09:43,715
Fine. Then let's take a boys-only bath together,

1203
01:09:43,787 --> 01:09:44,704
okay, Hodaka?

1204
01:09:44,728 --> 01:09:45,620
Wait, what?

1205
01:09:47,417 --> 01:09:49,856
This is the life.

1206
01:09:49,998 --> 01:09:51,237
What's this do?

1207
01:09:51,660 --> 01:09:52,716
Huh?

1208
01:09:54,726 --> 01:09:56,021
Whoa!

1209
01:09:57,307 --> 01:09:58,100
Your turn. Tag.

1210
01:09:58,124 --> 01:09:58,937
My turn. Tag.

1211
01:09:59,732 --> 01:10:01,820
Whoa, so many.

1212
01:10:02,010 --> 01:10:02,838
What do you want?

1213
01:10:02,862 --> 01:10:04,230
How about one of each, Sempai?

1214
01:10:04,272 --> 01:10:05,088
Are you sure?

1215
01:10:05,231 --> 01:10:07,145
Yeah. I got severance pay.

1216
01:10:07,288 --> 01:10:10,432
Hina, we're having a huge feast tonight!

1217
01:10:10,598 --> 01:10:11,765
I can't wait.

1218
01:10:15,853 --> 01:10:17,441
Sorry I took so long.

1219
01:10:18,544 --> 01:10:19,686
Uh, it-it's fine.

1220
01:10:30,541 --> 01:10:31,567
Bon appétit.

1221
01:10:32,291 --> 01:10:34,268
Hodaka, you want to try some of mine?

1222
01:10:34,355 --> 01:10:34,760
Mm.

1223
01:10:34,785 --> 01:10:35,391
Mmm!

1224
01:10:35,629 --> 01:10:36,579
Curry's good.

1225
01:10:36,675 --> 01:10:37,848
So are the noodles.

1226
01:10:37,872 --> 01:10:38,757
I want to try.

1227
01:10:39,574 --> 01:10:41,720
Hey, wait. I don't think those are ready yet.

1228
01:10:41,745 --> 01:10:43,554
It tastes better this way... Al dente.

1229
01:10:43,579 --> 01:10:46,334
My fortune cookie

1230
01:10:46,359 --> 01:10:48,392
Speaks of love again

1231
01:10:48,417 --> 01:10:49,924
Future's looking, looking bright...

1232
01:10:49,949 --> 01:10:52,806
It's that precious thing that is in your heart

1233
01:10:52,859 --> 01:10:55,596
It's the same thing that will soon depart, so...

1234
01:10:55,621 --> 01:10:57,653
God, if you really exist,

1235
01:10:58,293 --> 01:10:59,278
then I beg you.

1236
01:11:00,311 --> 01:11:01,678
This is more than enough.

1237
01:11:01,900 --> 01:11:03,545
We don't need anything else.

1238
01:11:04,503 --> 01:11:05,484
We'll manage somehow.

1239
01:11:05,509 --> 01:11:06,634
See how you like it!

1240
01:11:07,843 --> 01:11:08,954
So, please,

1241
01:11:09,805 --> 01:11:11,759
don't throw anything more at us,

1242
01:11:12,211 --> 01:11:15,463
but don't take anything more from us, either.

1243
01:11:16,518 --> 01:11:17,702
I'm begging you.

1244
01:11:18,290 --> 01:11:21,031
Please, God, let us stay like this.

1245
01:11:21,205 --> 01:11:23,859
Together, forever and ever.

1246
01:11:26,958 --> 01:11:28,452
Hina, here.

1247
01:11:28,849 --> 01:11:30,223
Happy 18th birthday.

1248
01:11:31,437 --> 01:11:32,081
Huh?

1249
01:11:32,519 --> 01:11:36,546
It's not much, but, uh, it's something
that I thought would look good on you.

1250
01:11:39,844 --> 01:11:40,830
Thanks.

1251
01:11:44,699 --> 01:11:45,517
Hey.

1252
01:11:46,637 --> 01:11:48,782
Can I ask you something?

1253
01:11:49,623 --> 01:11:51,446
Would you like the rain to stop?

1254
01:11:51,740 --> 01:11:53,518
Uh, yes. Yeah.

1255
01:12:01,787 --> 01:12:03,947
I'm a human sacrifice, they say.

1256
01:12:04,550 --> 01:12:05,026
Huh?

1257
01:12:06,148 --> 01:12:09,443
Natsumi was the one who told me
about the sunshine girl's fate.

1258
01:12:10,066 --> 01:12:12,822
If the Maiden gets sacrificed, then her body disappears,

1259
01:12:13,210 --> 01:12:15,705
but after that, the weather goes back to normal.

1260
01:12:17,439 --> 01:12:18,694
Come on, now.

1261
01:12:18,813 --> 01:12:20,948
You can't believe the stuff in those weird legends.

1262
01:12:20,973 --> 01:12:23,776
I mean, people don't disappear.

1263
01:12:36,554 --> 01:12:37,872
What are you looking at?

1264
01:12:37,927 --> 01:12:39,707
I'm not looking at anything!

1265
01:12:45,030 --> 01:12:46,889
I'm looking at you, Hina.

1266
01:12:48,646 --> 01:12:50,758
Come on. Why are you crying, Hodaka?

1267
01:12:53,930 --> 01:12:58,211
The more I pray for sunshine, the more my body fades away.

1268
01:12:59,141 --> 01:13:01,714
But if I end up dying from this...

1269
01:13:02,564 --> 01:13:04,837
we'll finally get our summers back.

1270
01:13:05,583 --> 01:13:07,002
Take care of Nagi for me.

1271
01:13:07,037 --> 01:13:07,656
No!

1272
01:13:07,767 --> 01:13:08,840
I won't!

1273
01:13:09,380 --> 01:13:10,963
'Cause you're not going anywhere.

1274
01:13:11,082 --> 01:13:12,977
We're all gonna live together.

1275
01:13:13,028 --> 01:13:13,726
Hodaka.

1276
01:13:14,068 --> 01:13:16,523
Hina, let's make a promise to each other

1277
01:13:16,809 --> 01:13:18,969
to always be together.

1278
01:13:21,546 --> 01:13:24,468
I'll get a job. I'll take care of us.

1279
01:13:24,658 --> 01:13:26,389
You don't have to be a sunshine girl anymore.

1280
01:13:26,510 --> 01:13:29,077
Your body will go back to normal, and then...

1281
01:13:49,433 --> 01:13:50,521
I had a dream.

1282
01:13:51,600 --> 01:13:52,865
I was still on the island.

1283
01:14:01,604 --> 01:14:02,755
I wanted to leave.

1284
01:14:03,294 --> 01:14:04,885
I pedaled as fast as I could.

1285
01:14:05,035 --> 01:14:08,045
I was desperate, wanting to go into the light.

1286
01:14:08,944 --> 01:14:10,350
When I finally reached it,

1287
01:14:10,810 --> 01:14:13,551
I discovered I had reached a dead end.

1288
01:14:14,489 --> 01:14:16,078
That's when I decided

1289
01:14:16,943 --> 01:14:18,772
that I was gonna go into that light.

1290
01:14:20,049 --> 01:14:21,175
And at the edge of it,

1291
01:14:22,442 --> 01:14:23,656
I found you.

1292
01:14:26,869 --> 01:14:28,187
I had a dream...

1293
01:14:29,617 --> 01:14:31,086
the day I met you.

1294
01:14:33,564 --> 01:14:34,064
Huh?

1295
01:14:34,575 --> 01:14:36,639
You looked like a lost kitten.

1296
01:14:38,827 --> 01:14:41,804
But you helped me find a reason to live.

1297
01:14:43,443 --> 01:14:47,063
I continued working as the sunshine
girl because it made me happy.

1298
01:14:47,874 --> 01:14:49,794
I liked making people smile.

1299
01:14:50,368 --> 01:14:52,386
I'm really glad I met you.

1300
01:14:53,945 --> 01:14:57,393
So, please, don't cry, Hodaka.

1301
01:15:12,274 --> 01:15:13,799
Where am I?

1302
01:15:17,487 --> 01:15:18,558
Hodaka.

1303
01:16:06,867 --> 01:16:07,999
Oh, no. Hina?

1304
01:16:08,102 --> 01:16:09,635
Where are you?!

1305
01:16:10,024 --> 01:16:10,818
Hina?!

1306
01:16:11,119 --> 01:16:12,104
Hina!

1307
01:16:12,192 --> 01:16:13,924
Hodaka, what is it?

1308
01:16:14,156 --> 01:16:15,839
Your sister's disappeared!

1309
01:16:15,864 --> 01:16:16,570
She's gone.

1310
01:16:18,151 --> 01:16:19,875
I was just dreaming...

1311
01:16:20,647 --> 01:16:23,338
that she disappeared into the sky.

1312
01:16:28,601 --> 01:16:29,601
It can't be.

1313
01:16:32,072 --> 01:16:32,857
Open the door.

1314
01:16:33,939 --> 01:16:34,717
Open up.

1315
01:16:34,836 --> 01:16:35,844
What?

1316
01:16:38,293 --> 01:16:40,168
Are you Hodaka Morishima?

1317
01:16:40,787 --> 01:16:43,123
You're the subject of a missing persons report.

1318
01:16:43,360 --> 01:16:46,856
We also believe that you're in
possession of an illegal firearm.

1319
01:16:47,039 --> 01:16:48,216
I need you to come to the station.

1320
01:16:48,241 --> 01:16:49,566
Let go of me!

1321
01:16:49,685 --> 01:16:50,943
It's okay. I'm not going to hurt you.

1322
01:16:50,968 --> 01:16:51,527
No!

1323
01:16:52,008 --> 01:16:52,999
We're taking a little trip.

1324
01:16:53,024 --> 01:16:53,840
Sempai!

1325
01:16:53,865 --> 01:16:56,098
Don't make this any harder than it has to be.

1326
01:17:09,066 --> 01:17:10,416
Why are you stopping?

1327
01:17:14,525 --> 01:17:19,378
After months of intense rain, the Kanto
region is finally seeing some brilliant sunshine.

1328
01:17:19,616 --> 01:17:22,684
The sun's rays are making yesterday's
storms seem like a crazy dream.

1329
01:17:22,709 --> 01:17:24,955
In a matter of hours, the weather has done a 180.

1330
01:17:24,979 --> 01:17:27,913
By 8:00 a.m., the temperature was 25 degrees Celsius.

1331
01:17:27,938 --> 01:17:31,050
Many areas adjacent to the
Arakawa River have remained flooded.

1332
01:17:31,085 --> 01:17:32,686
The trains are still not running.

1333
01:17:32,711 --> 01:17:35,536
The extent of the damage has yet to be ascertained.

1334
01:17:35,560 --> 01:17:39,170
Authorities say it will take at least
a week to restore municipal services,

1335
01:17:39,195 --> 01:17:42,284
as long as the weather remains clear.

1336
01:17:42,724 --> 01:17:43,539
The sky's clear.

1337
01:17:43,564 --> 01:17:44,905
Oh, so sunny.

1338
01:17:44,964 --> 01:17:46,346
Oh, it's so bright.

1339
01:17:46,576 --> 01:17:48,167
The sky's actually clear.

1340
01:17:48,347 --> 01:17:49,984
It's making me all emotional.

1341
01:17:50,009 --> 01:17:51,025
Well, it took a while,

1342
01:17:51,050 --> 01:17:52,859
but summer has finally arrived.

1343
01:18:03,537 --> 01:18:05,018
Hey. Hurry up.

1344
01:18:08,216 --> 01:18:09,598
This is Hina's.

1345
01:18:10,711 --> 01:18:12,038
She sacrificed.

1346
01:18:13,054 --> 01:18:14,760
Hina! What happened to you?!

1347
01:18:14,784 --> 01:18:15,524
Hey. Where are you going?

1348
01:18:15,549 --> 01:18:16,071
Hina!

1349
01:18:16,095 --> 01:18:17,013
Calm down.

1350
01:18:21,819 --> 01:18:24,258
I have something I need you to confirm for me.

1351
01:18:24,533 --> 01:18:28,530
The girl who disappeared last
night is 15-year-old Hina Amano.

1352
01:18:28,688 --> 01:18:29,508
Is that correct?

1353
01:18:31,130 --> 01:18:32,959
Do you have any idea where she could be?

1354
01:18:34,404 --> 01:18:35,247
She's 15?

1355
01:18:35,421 --> 01:18:36,899
Hina said she was older.

1356
01:18:37,118 --> 01:18:38,344
Isn't she 18?

1357
01:18:39,536 --> 01:18:43,046
She's been lying about her age on
her résumés and job applications.

1358
01:18:43,379 --> 01:18:46,669
I understand she needed to make a living,
but the truth is she's in middle school.

1359
01:18:47,273 --> 01:18:49,363
Or at least legally she's supposed to be.

1360
01:18:49,794 --> 01:18:50,730
You didn't know?

1361
01:18:52,613 --> 01:18:53,772
I don't believe it.

1362
01:18:54,742 --> 01:18:56,044
I'm the one who's older?

1363
01:18:58,596 --> 01:18:59,292
Oh, what a pain.

1364
01:18:59,317 --> 01:18:59,994
This whole time.

1365
01:19:00,986 --> 01:19:03,234
Hey. Do you know where she is or not?

1366
01:19:05,403 --> 01:19:06,714
The weather cleared up

1367
01:19:06,904 --> 01:19:09,685
only because Hina sacrificed herself in exchange.

1368
01:19:09,750 --> 01:19:10,249
Huh?

1369
01:19:10,871 --> 01:19:12,124
No one knows the truth!

1370
01:19:12,453 --> 01:19:14,578
No one knows her sacrifice.

1371
01:19:15,246 --> 01:19:16,422
What a pain.

1372
01:19:16,788 --> 01:19:18,575
Should we get a psychiatrist?

1373
01:19:23,399 --> 01:19:24,748
It's clear.

1374
01:19:29,722 --> 01:19:30,369
Huh.

1375
01:19:39,004 --> 01:19:40,837
Daddy, did you look outside?

1376
01:19:40,956 --> 01:19:42,404
Yeah, I did.

1377
01:19:42,642 --> 01:19:44,382
I had a dream about Hina.

1378
01:19:44,612 --> 01:19:46,530
She's the one who brought the sunshine back.

1379
01:19:46,582 --> 01:19:47,923
I know it.

1380
01:19:53,230 --> 01:19:55,868
Yeah. I think you might be right.

1381
01:19:59,515 --> 01:20:00,375
Excuse me.

1382
01:20:00,731 --> 01:20:03,614
Detective, I have a favor to ask you.

1383
01:20:04,552 --> 01:20:05,237
What is it?

1384
01:20:05,720 --> 01:20:06,633
Let me go.

1385
01:20:07,533 --> 01:20:09,280
I need to go out there and look for Hina.

1386
01:20:09,305 --> 01:20:10,765
It's my turn to help her now.

1387
01:20:10,845 --> 01:20:12,362
I'll come back as soon as I find her.

1388
01:20:12,854 --> 01:20:16,226
What you need to do is step in
here and answer some of my questions.

1389
01:20:16,266 --> 01:20:16,996
Understood?

1390
01:20:17,877 --> 01:20:20,618
Tell Yasui we're about to begin the interrogation.

1391
01:20:21,182 --> 01:20:21,802
Yes, sir.

1392
01:20:22,946 --> 01:20:23,389
Huh?

1393
01:20:23,535 --> 01:20:25,473
Hey! Get back here!

1394
01:20:28,539 --> 01:20:29,633
Stop running!

1395
01:20:29,668 --> 01:20:30,349
Come back!

1396
01:20:30,668 --> 01:20:32,035
Someone stop him!

1397
01:20:32,060 --> 01:20:33,833
Stop! I said stop!

1398
01:20:36,516 --> 01:20:37,392
Do not let the boy in the white T-shirt

1399
01:20:37,417 --> 01:20:38,854
leave the building.

1400
01:20:39,013 --> 01:20:40,606
Stop that kid!

1401
01:20:41,998 --> 01:20:44,000
Wait! Stop!

1402
01:20:48,991 --> 01:20:50,491
Hey! Come back here!

1403
01:20:52,835 --> 01:20:54,086
What the hell?!

1404
01:20:54,430 --> 01:20:55,290
That little shit.

1405
01:20:55,417 --> 01:20:56,443
Cut him off.

1406
01:20:56,753 --> 01:20:57,678
You go that way.

1407
01:20:57,702 --> 01:20:58,443
Yes, sir.

1408
01:21:05,809 --> 01:21:06,642
No!

1409
01:21:15,325 --> 01:21:16,359
Hodaka!

1410
01:21:16,582 --> 01:21:17,177
Huh?

1411
01:21:19,608 --> 01:21:20,512
Natsumi?

1412
01:21:20,720 --> 01:21:21,911
What are you doing?

1413
01:21:22,416 --> 01:21:24,163
I'm going to get Hina back.

1414
01:21:24,274 --> 01:21:24,925
Huh?

1415
01:21:27,154 --> 01:21:28,125
Get on.

1416
01:21:34,719 --> 01:21:35,832
Goddamn punk!

1417
01:21:37,118 --> 01:21:39,074
While you were at the station, Nagi called.

1418
01:21:39,455 --> 01:21:42,553
He said Hina had disappeared and
that the police had arrested you.

1419
01:21:42,704 --> 01:21:43,491
Where is he?

1420
01:21:43,610 --> 01:21:45,811
At a child service center.

1421
01:21:50,284 --> 01:21:51,324
No going back.

1422
01:21:51,777 --> 01:21:53,566
We're about to become outlaws.

1423
01:21:53,764 --> 01:21:55,996
Breaking the law!

1424
01:21:56,623 --> 01:21:58,689
All right, partner, where we headed?

1425
01:22:02,289 --> 01:22:04,523
What? Another visitor?

1426
01:22:07,470 --> 01:22:09,175
Yeah, and it's another girl.

1427
01:22:09,199 --> 01:22:10,877
He sure is popular.

1428
01:22:13,437 --> 01:22:14,518
Hello, Nagi.

1429
01:22:14,605 --> 01:22:16,687
Ayane, I'm so glad you could make it.

1430
01:22:17,155 --> 01:22:18,526
Kana, this is Ayane.

1431
01:22:18,550 --> 01:22:19,380
Nice to meet you.

1432
01:22:19,405 --> 01:22:20,957
Ayane, this is Kana.

1433
01:22:20,981 --> 01:22:21,771
My pleasure.

1434
01:22:21,843 --> 01:22:23,309
And that's Officer Sasaki.

1435
01:22:23,804 --> 01:22:25,742
She's going to be watching over me all day.

1436
01:22:25,767 --> 01:22:27,219
Wow. That's so cool.

1437
01:22:27,244 --> 01:22:28,540
It's like you're a celebrity.

1438
01:22:28,691 --> 01:22:29,149
How do you do?

1439
01:22:29,173 --> 01:22:29,820
Nice to meet you.

1440
01:22:30,891 --> 01:22:32,551
Thank you both so much for coming.

1441
01:22:32,853 --> 01:22:35,065
I'm sure you must have been surprised by my call.

1442
01:22:35,102 --> 01:22:36,054
I was.

1443
01:22:36,183 --> 01:22:37,899
When I heard they took you in custody,

1444
01:22:38,018 --> 01:22:39,187
my heart almost stopped.

1445
01:22:39,243 --> 01:22:41,505
Me, too. Mine's still pounding.

1446
01:22:41,530 --> 01:22:44,285
Nagi, if you touch my chest, you can feel it.

1447
01:22:44,310 --> 01:22:45,495
Yeah, she's right.

1448
01:22:45,598 --> 01:22:47,282
Oh, I do feel it.

1449
01:22:51,175 --> 01:22:52,729
Um, excuse me.

1450
01:22:52,753 --> 01:22:53,304
Yes?

1451
01:22:53,367 --> 01:22:56,757
It's-it's my first time here, so I
don't know my way around, and, uh...

1452
01:22:56,781 --> 01:22:57,595
Uh-huh.

1453
01:22:58,040 --> 01:22:59,764
Uh, where's the bathroom?

1454
01:23:00,168 --> 01:23:01,567
Oh.

1455
01:23:04,918 --> 01:23:06,468
Thanks. I owe you one.

1456
01:23:06,650 --> 01:23:08,518
You better. I can't believe you.

1457
01:23:08,645 --> 01:23:11,648
Calling your ex to help you out with something like this?

1458
01:23:12,259 --> 01:23:12,992
Take it.

1459
01:23:13,301 --> 01:23:14,259
Turn around.

1460
01:23:14,372 --> 01:23:16,167
We still need to swap clothes.

1461
01:23:26,299 --> 01:23:29,207
Mr. Keisuke Suga. Good to see you again.

1462
01:23:29,540 --> 01:23:30,508
You again?

1463
01:23:30,637 --> 01:23:31,415
What do you want?

1464
01:23:31,697 --> 01:23:34,934
Looks like the weather's finally
back to the way it should be, huh?

1465
01:23:35,545 --> 01:23:38,836
I told you already, I know nothing about that runaway.

1466
01:23:39,090 --> 01:23:41,124
Would you mind if we took a look around your office?

1467
01:23:41,149 --> 01:23:42,332
What? Hey. It's not a good time.

1468
01:23:42,356 --> 01:23:44,034
Oh, it's really flooded, huh? That's too bad.

1469
01:23:44,058 --> 01:23:46,058
You're not gonna find him down there.

1470
01:23:47,321 --> 01:23:48,837
Yeah, we know.

1471
01:23:48,862 --> 01:23:51,196
This is embarrassing, but, uh, the truth is...

1472
01:23:51,286 --> 01:23:53,414
Huh? What do you mean, he ran away?

1473
01:23:53,442 --> 01:23:55,138
From the police station?

1474
01:23:56,170 --> 01:23:57,775
An abandoned building in Yoyogi?

1475
01:23:57,800 --> 01:23:59,735
Yeah. It's where she became a sunshine...

1476
01:23:59,759 --> 01:24:00,405
Duck!

1477
01:24:02,082 --> 01:24:05,442
She said she became connected
with the sky on that building's roof

1478
01:24:05,625 --> 01:24:07,644
and that's how she became the sunshine girl.

1479
01:24:07,715 --> 01:24:10,114
So, I think that's where I have to go.

1480
01:24:15,381 --> 01:24:16,619
Oh, great!

1481
01:24:19,736 --> 01:24:21,151
Hey, on the scooter!

1482
01:24:21,252 --> 01:24:21,827
Pull over!

1483
01:24:22,770 --> 01:24:24,127
Hold on tight.

1484
01:24:31,317 --> 01:24:32,278
Hold on!

1485
01:24:33,114 --> 01:24:34,271
I think that maybe...

1486
01:24:34,295 --> 01:24:34,704
What?

1487
01:24:34,807 --> 01:24:37,435
That I'm totally awesome? I know!

1488
01:24:37,580 --> 01:24:39,281
I was born for this stuff.

1489
01:24:39,352 --> 01:24:44,166
That's it... I'm gonna be a motorcycle
cop and catch anyone who speeds!

1490
01:24:44,254 --> 01:24:46,707
They're not gonna hire you after this!

1491
01:24:49,322 --> 01:24:52,206
We have a theory about why the kid escaped.

1492
01:24:52,278 --> 01:24:55,566
We think he may be trying to
search for the girl who he was with.

1493
01:24:55,971 --> 01:25:00,675
You see, he told us a few things that
frankly sounded like science fiction.

1494
01:25:01,071 --> 01:25:06,132
He seems to believe that the girl disappeared
in exchange for the good weather returning.

1495
01:25:07,374 --> 01:25:08,947
That's ridiculous.

1496
01:25:08,979 --> 01:25:10,471
Don't tell me you believe him.

1497
01:25:10,496 --> 01:25:12,014
No, of course I don't.

1498
01:25:12,633 --> 01:25:16,143
But what I do believe is that he's throwing his life away.

1499
01:25:17,915 --> 01:25:20,379
And all of it is just because of some girl.

1500
01:25:20,815 --> 01:25:22,396
To be honest with you,

1501
01:25:22,701 --> 01:25:25,479
I envy the kid to feel that passionately.

1502
01:25:26,821 --> 01:25:29,617
What's the point in sharing that? It doesn't change much.

1503
01:25:31,741 --> 01:25:32,233
Huh?

1504
01:25:33,679 --> 01:25:35,451
Mr. Suga, are you, uh...

1505
01:25:35,935 --> 01:25:36,507
Huh?

1506
01:25:38,723 --> 01:25:39,686
Are you okay?

1507
01:25:40,091 --> 01:25:41,114
Why do you ask?

1508
01:25:41,971 --> 01:25:44,378
Well, it's just that you, uh...

1509
01:25:45,278 --> 01:25:46,460
you're crying.

1510
01:25:55,739 --> 01:25:56,884
This is bad.

1511
01:25:59,278 --> 01:26:00,425
We're gonna jump it.

1512
01:26:00,460 --> 01:26:01,843
Huh?

1513
01:26:02,216 --> 01:26:03,797
No. Wait.

1514
01:26:11,305 --> 01:26:13,204
Ugh, it's the end of the line.

1515
01:26:13,386 --> 01:26:13,872
Hurry. Get out of here.

1516
01:26:13,907 --> 01:26:14,793
Go on.

1517
01:26:19,140 --> 01:26:20,807
Thank you. Wish me luck.

1518
01:26:25,781 --> 01:26:28,030
Hodaka!

1519
01:26:28,689 --> 01:26:30,211
Never give up!

1520
01:26:54,042 --> 01:26:54,765
Hina.

1521
01:26:56,209 --> 01:26:58,489
Hina. Hina, Hina!

1522
01:26:59,920 --> 01:27:00,602
Hina?

1523
01:27:01,355 --> 01:27:02,557
Hina, are you there?

1524
01:27:03,257 --> 01:27:04,440
Hina!

1525
01:27:06,085 --> 01:27:07,786
Hey, Hodaka.

1526
01:27:08,334 --> 01:27:09,892
It's gonna clear up.

1527
01:27:12,346 --> 01:27:14,388
It's for you, but don't tell.

1528
01:27:14,578 --> 01:27:16,406
Unless you want to have chowder for dinner again.

1529
01:27:16,548 --> 01:27:18,773
Does it hurt? Let me guess... You ran away from home?

1530
01:27:18,798 --> 01:27:21,411
Too bad you can't enjoy Tokyo with all this rain.

1531
01:27:21,570 --> 01:27:22,707
You're younger than me.

1532
01:27:22,771 --> 01:27:24,859
I'll be 18 in approximately a month.

1533
01:27:24,884 --> 01:27:25,997
You should treat me with respect.

1534
01:27:26,022 --> 01:27:27,409
Hodaka, have you had lunch yet?

1535
01:27:27,570 --> 01:27:28,847
You just sit right there.

1536
01:27:28,903 --> 01:27:30,381
How do you like living in Tokyo?

1537
01:27:30,420 --> 01:27:31,835
Huh? Uh...

1538
01:27:32,041 --> 01:27:34,586
I don't feel like I'm suffocating anymore.

1539
01:27:34,621 --> 01:27:36,897
Well, that's great, right?

1540
01:27:37,047 --> 01:27:39,251
I think I'm in love...

1541
01:27:39,584 --> 01:27:41,919
with this job as the sunshine girl.

1542
01:27:42,236 --> 01:27:43,028
And so...

1543
01:27:43,492 --> 01:27:45,367
thank you, Hodaka.

1544
01:27:48,662 --> 01:27:49,295
Hey, hey, look.

1545
01:27:49,319 --> 01:27:50,744
There's someone on the tracks!

1546
01:27:50,769 --> 01:27:51,655
Who is that?

1547
01:27:51,679 --> 01:27:52,302
Stop!

1548
01:27:52,524 --> 01:27:53,427
You can't be here!

1549
01:27:53,451 --> 01:27:54,263
Come back! It's dangerous!

1550
01:27:54,288 --> 01:27:55,707
Hey, hey! What are you doing?

1551
01:27:55,742 --> 01:27:57,959
This place is off-limits!

1552
01:28:00,532 --> 01:28:01,516
What is he doing?

1553
01:28:01,694 --> 01:28:02,619
What is he doing?

1554
01:28:02,643 --> 01:28:03,326
That's so crazy.

1555
01:28:03,350 --> 01:28:04,661
There's someone running up there.

1556
01:28:04,685 --> 01:28:05,821
He's gonna get himself arrested.

1557
01:28:05,845 --> 01:28:06,363
Do you see that?

1558
01:28:06,388 --> 01:28:07,659
Some people are such idiots.

1559
01:28:22,470 --> 01:28:23,336
I'm sorry.

1560
01:28:23,470 --> 01:28:24,852
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

1561
01:28:24,877 --> 01:28:26,204
I'm so sorry, Hina!

1562
01:28:26,450 --> 01:28:28,318
I made you do that sunshine girl job,

1563
01:28:28,556 --> 01:28:31,550
but in the end, you were the one
who had to deal with the consequences.

1564
01:28:31,724 --> 01:28:32,145
Hey.

1565
01:28:32,351 --> 01:28:33,996
Can I ask you something?

1566
01:28:35,244 --> 01:28:37,158
Would you like the rain to stop?

1567
01:29:06,046 --> 01:29:07,126
Mr. Suga?

1568
01:29:08,184 --> 01:29:10,115
People are looking for you, Hodaka.

1569
01:29:10,321 --> 01:29:11,481
How did you find me?

1570
01:29:11,663 --> 01:29:12,494
Look at you.

1571
01:29:12,735 --> 01:29:14,279
Do you have any idea what you're doing?

1572
01:29:14,304 --> 01:29:16,113
You don't get it. Hina's gone!

1573
01:29:16,763 --> 01:29:17,915
And it's my fault.

1574
01:29:18,051 --> 01:29:19,791
The sunshine girl job was my idea.

1575
01:29:19,816 --> 01:29:20,960
Hodaka, calm down.

1576
01:29:20,985 --> 01:29:22,239
That's why I have to help her!

1577
01:29:25,368 --> 01:29:26,098
I have to go.

1578
01:29:27,449 --> 01:29:28,172
Hey, wait.

1579
01:29:28,197 --> 01:29:29,349
Where are you...

1580
01:29:29,905 --> 01:29:32,414
I can make it to Heaven if I just go through that.

1581
01:29:34,569 --> 01:29:34,988
What?

1582
01:29:35,013 --> 01:29:35,916
Have you lost it?

1583
01:29:35,940 --> 01:29:37,197
She's somewhere in the sky.

1584
01:29:37,222 --> 01:29:38,913
I can get there if I use the stairs!

1585
01:29:38,953 --> 01:29:40,445
Hodaka, stop this.

1586
01:29:40,470 --> 01:29:41,847
There's no way she's up there.

1587
01:29:42,657 --> 01:29:44,001
Snap out of it!

1588
01:29:45,834 --> 01:29:47,501
What's gotten into you?

1589
01:29:47,876 --> 01:29:49,565
You have to go back to the police station.

1590
01:29:49,589 --> 01:29:51,401
If you explain it to them, they'll understand.

1591
01:29:51,425 --> 01:29:52,935
You haven't done anything wrong.

1592
01:29:53,375 --> 01:29:57,963
You can't keep running away from your
problems. They'll catch up to you. You know this.

1593
01:29:58,099 --> 01:30:00,410
We've located the vehicle. We're going in.

1594
01:30:01,166 --> 01:30:02,835
Look don't worry.

1595
01:30:03,033 --> 01:30:04,487
I'll come with you, okay?

1596
01:30:04,789 --> 01:30:06,665
Then we can explain everything together.

1597
01:30:06,729 --> 01:30:07,917
Let go of me!

1598
01:30:08,126 --> 01:30:09,334
I said let go!

1599
01:30:09,493 --> 01:30:10,061
Cut it out!

1600
01:30:10,085 --> 01:30:10,822
Let go!

1601
01:30:12,886 --> 01:30:14,108
Get off of me!

1602
01:30:18,669 --> 01:30:19,951
Get out of my way.

1603
01:30:21,617 --> 01:30:23,755
Hodaka, what are you doing?

1604
01:30:23,865 --> 01:30:27,161
Let me go to Hina. I have to see her!

1605
01:30:49,053 --> 01:30:50,268
Hodaka Morishima!

1606
01:30:50,506 --> 01:30:52,042
Drop the gun!

1607
01:30:52,066 --> 01:30:52,672
Whoa.

1608
01:30:52,926 --> 01:30:54,784
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

1609
01:30:54,809 --> 01:30:55,620
Everybody, calm down.

1610
01:30:56,049 --> 01:30:57,479
This is a misunderstanding.

1611
01:30:57,504 --> 01:30:59,053
Don't shoot. I can explain.

1612
01:30:59,355 --> 01:31:00,380
Hodaka, come on.

1613
01:31:02,318 --> 01:31:03,862
Huh? What are you...?

1614
01:31:04,097 --> 01:31:06,361
Don't do this. Put the weapon down.

1615
01:31:06,681 --> 01:31:08,300
I don't want to shoot you.

1616
01:31:21,139 --> 01:31:21,847
Hodaka.

1617
01:31:22,028 --> 01:31:23,114
It's gonna be okay.

1618
01:31:23,149 --> 01:31:24,325
Just do what they say.

1619
01:31:24,618 --> 01:31:25,859
What's wrong with you guys, anyway?

1620
01:31:25,884 --> 01:31:27,097
Give him a break.

1621
01:31:27,122 --> 01:31:28,456
He's just a kid. It's...

1622
01:31:28,481 --> 01:31:29,888
Why can't you leave me alone?

1623
01:31:30,086 --> 01:31:31,620
Why are you standing in my way?

1624
01:31:31,953 --> 01:31:32,991
You don't know anything,

1625
01:31:33,026 --> 01:31:34,941
because you choose to ignore the truth.

1626
01:31:35,338 --> 01:31:36,345
So, please...

1627
01:31:37,181 --> 01:31:39,587
All I want is to see her again.

1628
01:31:40,627 --> 01:31:42,201
I have to see her!

1629
01:31:46,342 --> 01:31:48,128
Stay down!

1630
01:31:49,892 --> 01:31:51,331
Let me go!

1631
01:31:51,775 --> 01:31:54,366
Get your hands off Hodaka right now.

1632
01:31:54,969 --> 01:31:56,186
Get off of him!

1633
01:31:58,481 --> 01:31:59,997
Son of a...

1634
01:32:00,434 --> 01:32:01,737
Hodaka, go!

1635
01:32:01,825 --> 01:32:02,929
What the...

1636
01:32:05,633 --> 01:32:06,537
Hold it!

1637
01:32:07,500 --> 01:32:08,381
Hodaka!

1638
01:32:09,785 --> 01:32:10,708
Nagi?

1639
01:32:11,852 --> 01:32:13,688
Hey, what do you think you're doing?

1640
01:32:13,790 --> 01:32:16,691
This is your fault, Hodaka, so you have to fix it!

1641
01:32:16,779 --> 01:32:18,653
Go and bring my sister back!

1642
01:32:53,445 --> 01:32:54,310
God...

1643
01:32:55,141 --> 01:32:57,121
please, please.

1644
01:32:57,607 --> 01:32:58,623
Please!

1645
01:32:58,945 --> 01:33:00,300
I beg you!

1646
01:33:30,130 --> 01:33:31,765
Is that fish?

1647
01:33:32,045 --> 01:33:33,138
In the sky?

1648
01:33:59,292 --> 01:34:01,368
Hina!

1649
01:34:18,956 --> 01:34:20,058
Hina!

1650
01:34:22,094 --> 01:34:23,694
Hina!

1651
01:34:34,708 --> 01:34:36,334
Hina!

1652
01:34:42,873 --> 01:34:43,647
Hina!

1653
01:34:43,706 --> 01:34:44,524
Hodaka!

1654
01:34:51,556 --> 01:34:52,239
Hina!

1655
01:34:52,264 --> 01:34:53,160
Hodaka!

1656
01:34:54,106 --> 01:34:55,273
Just jump!

1657
01:35:06,658 --> 01:35:08,356
Hina, I found you.

1658
01:35:08,479 --> 01:35:10,416
Hodaka. Hodaka!

1659
01:35:10,495 --> 01:35:11,791
Don't let go of my hands.

1660
01:35:30,524 --> 01:35:31,524
Hina!

1661
01:35:32,407 --> 01:35:33,637
Hodaka!

1662
01:35:40,528 --> 01:35:41,855
Let's go home.

1663
01:35:42,882 --> 01:35:45,035
But if I do, the weather,

1664
01:35:45,084 --> 01:35:46,485
it-it will go back to...

1665
01:35:46,509 --> 01:35:47,069
Let it.

1666
01:35:47,139 --> 01:35:49,165
I don't care. You've done enough.

1667
01:35:49,276 --> 01:35:52,151
You don't have to be the sunshine girl anymore!

1668
01:36:05,103 --> 01:36:07,508
I don't care if I ever see the sun again.

1669
01:36:08,153 --> 01:36:11,503
I care about you. I don't care about blue skies.

1670
01:36:12,610 --> 01:36:13,983
It'll be okay.

1671
01:36:14,267 --> 01:36:16,135
Let the weather stay crazy.

1672
01:36:55,915 --> 01:36:57,355
Pray for yourself...

1673
01:36:59,309 --> 01:37:00,103
Hina.

1674
01:37:16,559 --> 01:37:17,360
Huh?

1675
01:37:22,372 --> 01:37:23,682
Hodaka.

1676
01:38:08,747 --> 01:38:10,892
The rain started falling again that day,

1677
01:38:11,440 --> 01:38:13,339
and since then, it hasn't stopped.

1678
01:38:14,069 --> 01:38:17,428
Slowly, it sank Tokyo, where it remains,

1679
01:38:17,898 --> 01:38:19,230
submerged in water.

1680
01:38:19,718 --> 01:38:23,097
The rain's still falling three years later.

1681
01:38:38,276 --> 01:38:43,554
The garden where we've grown

1682
01:38:44,422 --> 01:38:47,525
When we look back

1683
01:38:47,639 --> 01:38:50,929
It went so fast

1684
01:38:50,991 --> 01:38:56,725
Now we must Say goodbye

1685
01:38:57,203 --> 01:38:59,610
We're leaving here

1686
01:38:59,745 --> 01:39:00,961
After all this...

1687
01:39:01,779 --> 01:39:03,447
 What's left for me to say?

1688
01:39:05,467 --> 01:39:07,928
Excuse me. Hodaka?

1689
01:39:09,906 --> 01:39:13,952
Uh, i-is it true that you're moving to Tokyo?

1690
01:39:13,987 --> 01:39:15,324
Uh, yeah.

1691
01:39:15,938 --> 01:39:17,345
Just ask him already.

1692
01:39:17,543 --> 01:39:18,870
It's your last chance.

1693
01:39:18,949 --> 01:39:19,608
Mm...

1694
01:39:19,719 --> 01:39:22,130
Wait a minute. Could this be...

1695
01:39:22,155 --> 01:39:24,295
Um, I just... I...

1696
01:39:24,551 --> 01:39:26,751
Well, there's something that
I've always wanted to ask you.

1697
01:39:26,776 --> 01:39:27,732
I don't believe it.

1698
01:39:27,857 --> 01:39:29,326
My first love confession?

1699
01:39:29,755 --> 01:39:31,677
Uh, Hodaka...

1700
01:39:32,086 --> 01:39:32,584
Huh?

1701
01:39:32,741 --> 01:39:33,638
I...

1702
01:39:34,045 --> 01:39:36,413
I heard you were wanted by the police in Tokyo.

1703
01:39:36,540 --> 01:39:37,460
Is it true?

1704
01:39:38,708 --> 01:39:39,264
Huh?

1705
01:39:43,110 --> 01:39:44,388
That same summer,

1706
01:39:44,927 --> 01:39:46,049
three years ago,

1707
01:39:47,041 --> 01:39:48,630
I ended up getting arrested.

1708
01:39:49,774 --> 01:39:51,530
They charged me, and I stood trial.

1709
01:39:52,705 --> 01:39:55,439
I had to be on probation until I graduated high school.

1710
01:39:56,494 --> 01:39:59,323
The island, my parents' house, school...

1711
01:39:59,760 --> 01:40:02,333
They were all the same old places where I spent my life.

1712
01:40:02,470 --> 01:40:05,052
But, actually, I was just biding my time,

1713
01:40:05,172 --> 01:40:06,840
waiting for graduation to come.

1714
01:40:08,874 --> 01:40:09,780
That day...

1715
01:40:11,644 --> 01:40:13,434
was the last time I saw Hina.

1716
01:40:14,807 --> 01:40:17,200
I have no idea what I'll think.

1717
01:40:19,226 --> 01:40:21,934
I haven't seen Tokyo since after it changed.

1718
01:40:23,061 --> 01:40:25,541
And I have no idea what I'll say to her.

1719
01:40:27,665 --> 01:40:30,638
Here's tomorrow's weather forecast for the Kanto region.

1720
01:40:31,008 --> 01:40:32,341
A full day of rain is predicted.

1721
01:40:32,365 --> 01:40:34,995
Now if I could just find a job.

1722
01:40:35,067 --> 01:40:38,480
Heavy rainfall in the mountain
regions. Lower, in the metropolitan areas,

1723
01:40:38,504 --> 01:40:42,291
there is a chance of the rain letting
up periodically throughout the day.

1724
01:40:42,918 --> 01:40:48,509
The high will be 59 degrees Fahrenheit, with the
same or slightly hotter temps in surrounding areas.

1725
01:40:49,303 --> 01:40:50,313
Oh, right.

1726
01:40:50,870 --> 01:40:52,243
Speaking of jobs...

1727
01:40:53,770 --> 01:40:56,105
Now for the forecast for the rest of the week.

1728
01:40:56,200 --> 01:40:57,755
It looks like rain is expected every day.

1729
01:40:57,857 --> 01:40:58,821
The site's still up.

1730
01:41:05,604 --> 01:41:07,632
There was still one unanswered request.

1731
01:41:08,021 --> 01:41:09,395
It was from two years ago.

1732
01:41:09,586 --> 01:41:11,826
Next stop: Takashimadaira.

1733
01:41:11,993 --> 01:41:13,309
Takashimadaira.

1734
01:41:13,334 --> 01:41:16,068
Oh, it's you. Are you alone?

1735
01:41:16,346 --> 01:41:18,150
Where's your sunshine girl?

1736
01:41:18,229 --> 01:41:21,001
Oh, she's no longer a sunshine girl.

1737
01:41:21,429 --> 01:41:24,415
Actually, it's why I'm here... To tell you that.

1738
01:41:24,840 --> 01:41:26,968
Uh, thanks, but I'm okay.

1739
01:41:27,817 --> 01:41:30,008
So, how long have you been living here?

1740
01:41:30,457 --> 01:41:32,633
Last time, weren't you in a house downtown somewhere?

1741
01:41:32,832 --> 01:41:33,966
I had to move.

1742
01:41:33,991 --> 01:41:36,192
The entire area is underwater now.

1743
01:41:36,462 --> 01:41:37,662
Sorry about that.

1744
01:41:37,799 --> 01:41:40,047
Why are you apologizing?

1745
01:41:44,781 --> 01:41:49,464
Did you know the entire area of
Tokyo used to be under the sea?

1746
01:41:50,052 --> 01:41:53,769
I think, until about 200 years ago.

1747
01:41:55,197 --> 01:41:56,883
Back when it was called Edo,

1748
01:41:57,082 --> 01:41:58,649
Tokyo was just a bay.

1749
01:41:59,155 --> 01:42:03,135
Little by little, humans... As well as
the weather... Changed this landscape.

1750
01:42:04,492 --> 01:42:05,709
Look at it now.

1751
01:42:05,962 --> 01:42:07,607
It's sort of reverted back,

1752
01:42:07,830 --> 01:42:09,816
back to its original self.

1753
01:42:11,620 --> 01:42:14,996
What is wrong with you? You've been thinking
about this crap for the last three years?

1754
01:42:15,530 --> 01:42:17,106
Hey, don't call it crap.

1755
01:42:17,130 --> 01:42:18,254
Stop acting like a kid.

1756
01:42:18,286 --> 01:42:20,716
You're about to start college.
You should focus on other things.

1757
01:42:20,764 --> 01:42:23,061
Yeah, but the two of us did something.

1758
01:42:23,172 --> 01:42:25,038
Did what? You think you caused this?

1759
01:42:25,063 --> 01:42:27,819
You really think you're
responsible for changing the world?

1760
01:42:30,291 --> 01:42:32,047
That's precisely why I called it crap.

1761
01:42:32,372 --> 01:42:34,000
You don't matter in the scheme of things.

1762
01:42:34,025 --> 01:42:35,543
Don't flatter yourself.

1763
01:42:35,646 --> 01:42:37,440
Oh. Check it out.

1764
01:42:37,551 --> 01:42:39,142
It's from my last date with my daughter.

1765
01:42:39,252 --> 01:42:41,963
Natsumi and Nagi were the third and fourth wheel, though.

1766
01:42:42,224 --> 01:42:47,180
Now, for crying out loud, will you stop
brooding over all this nonsense and just go see her?

1767
01:42:47,323 --> 01:42:48,770
I don't know why you haven't already.

1768
01:42:48,795 --> 01:42:52,614
I was on probation, so I wasn't supposed
to, and I didn't want to cause her any trouble.

1769
01:42:52,728 --> 01:42:55,430
Plus, even if I wanted to, she doesn't have a cell phone.

1770
01:42:55,533 --> 01:42:57,051
Also, I'm super nervous.

1771
01:42:57,162 --> 01:42:59,138
I don't even know what to say to her.

1772
01:43:05,360 --> 01:43:05,938
Rain?

1773
01:43:06,543 --> 01:43:07,965
You've gotten so big.

1774
01:43:08,721 --> 01:43:11,929
Go on. Get out of here. Can't
you see I got work to do? Beat it.

1775
01:43:12,040 --> 01:43:13,925
Go and find her. You know you want to.

1776
01:43:14,812 --> 01:43:16,062
Thank you for your time.

1777
01:43:16,150 --> 01:43:17,277
Nice to meet you.

1778
01:43:18,229 --> 01:43:18,697
Hey.

1779
01:43:18,927 --> 01:43:19,578
Huh?

1780
01:43:20,281 --> 01:43:23,107
Don't sweat the small stuff, big man.

1781
01:43:24,095 --> 01:43:25,476
The world is crazy.

1782
01:43:25,982 --> 01:43:28,351
It always has been, always will be.

1783
01:43:38,189 --> 01:43:39,817
The next stop is Hamamatsucho.

1784
01:43:39,852 --> 01:43:41,830
So where do you want to go to lunch?

1785
01:43:41,854 --> 01:43:43,498
You're always so incredibly positive.

1786
01:43:43,522 --> 01:43:44,525
You really think so?

1787
01:43:44,549 --> 01:43:45,267
The flowers should be

1788
01:43:45,291 --> 01:43:46,075
in full bloom.

1789
01:43:46,099 --> 01:43:46,919
That's what I hear.

1790
01:43:57,765 --> 01:44:00,545
Used to be under the sea.

1791
01:44:02,221 --> 01:44:03,595
The world's crazy.

1792
01:44:03,937 --> 01:44:05,877
Always has been, always will be.

1793
01:44:08,928 --> 01:44:13,003
So that means it's no one's fault that it's like this now.

1794
01:44:13,286 --> 01:44:14,925
Is this what I should say to her?

1795
01:44:15,885 --> 01:44:16,927
I don't know.

1796
01:44:48,835 --> 01:44:50,995
No. They're wrong.

1797
01:44:51,185 --> 01:44:54,650
That day, I... No, we changed the world.

1798
01:44:54,872 --> 01:44:56,060
I made a choice.

1799
01:44:56,255 --> 01:44:57,334
I chose her.

1800
01:44:57,572 --> 01:44:58,955
I chose this world,

1801
01:44:59,187 --> 01:45:01,252
and I choose to live in it!

1802
01:45:02,314 --> 01:45:03,506
Hina!

1803
01:45:09,214 --> 01:45:10,435
Hodaka!

1804
01:45:17,738 --> 01:45:19,417
Hodaka, what's wrong?

1805
01:45:19,771 --> 01:45:20,757
Are you okay?

1806
01:45:21,759 --> 01:45:22,545
Yeah.

1807
01:45:24,587 --> 01:45:25,594
Yeah, I'm fine.

1808
01:45:25,880 --> 01:45:27,096
You know what, Hina?

1809
01:45:28,503 --> 01:45:29,981
We're gonna be all right.

